ABOUT PARADYN

We are researchers, developers and entrepreneurs with decades of experience in solving real-world problems. For 10+ years Paradyn continues to shake up the global mining industry with our novel cloud-based technology. Servicing domestic and international clients who span the globe our BlendOpt software discovers 10s of millions of dollars in profit using our proprietary mathematical optimisation and descriptive analytics.

Our continued success translating innovation to business outcome is pushing us to grow and we seek outstanding people to join our exceptional Technical Delivery Team.

OUR CULTURE

We know that smart and creative people realise their full potential when granted autonomy. We deeply value our people and their skills and input. We know they’re creative because they deliver novel solutions to challenging problems every day.

We know they have strong emotional intelligence because they place effort in communication to facilitate alignment within multi-disciplinary teams.

We know they have exciting futures because they self-reflect and invite opportunities to grow and learn.

Competence drives freedom. Our people are constantly growing and learning. They acquire and apply domain knowledge to ensure technical brilliance translates to exciting customer results. Our people learn and build upon repeatable systems and processes. We continually innovate, increasing our responsiveness and our individual and collective success. Our meritocracy creates a pathway for you unbound by age, background or location.

Freedom comes from consistently demonstrated competence. Freedom to make critical design choices, freedom to work flexible hours, freedom to realise your potential, freedom to fail and improve.

ROLE

We’re looking for talented and energetic STEM-centric people to join our Technical Delivery Team (TDT).

Yours is an important role covering many aspects of technical software delivery. You’ll use your well-rounded analytical skills to evaluate and understand our clients’ mining value-chain modelling requirements. Then, apply your first-class mathematics and software engineering skills to configure and build supply-chain models of operations utilising our proprietary algorithms and software.

The TDT applies test driven development, rigorous hypothesis testing, agile project delivery concepts, systems science, and theory of constraints to construct models and analyse optimisation results gaining deep insights into the planning decisions and challenges of some of the world’s largest mining operations.

WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING

To deliver our managed software solutions for our clients, you:

 * work independently and conscientiously, as part of a positive and supportive agile team
 * participate in all aspects of the solution delivery process, including requirements gathering, solution ideation and design, delivery, implementation
 * apply test driven development to design mining value chain models utilising BlendOpt software
 * engineer maintainable code, solve problems, create new features, fix bugs, perform code peer-reviews and testing, and provide support
 * analyse results and tune the BlendOpt optimisation algorithms to meet unique end-user requirements
 * customise data visualisation and queries within BlendOpt using Paradyn’s proprietary interactive dashboards
 * analyse and interpret optimised production plans, considering client-specific value drivers and constraints
 * client liaison, including technical sales support, with end users (mining engineers, logistics coordinators, process engineers)
 * support other team members in the review of solution designs and code reviews for other projects.

WHAT YOU WON’T BE DOING

 * Making subjective judgment calls. We are a data-driven organization, and each decision needs to be substantiated by evidence.

TECHNICAL AND OTHER REQUIREMENTS

We’re seeking a technically experienced individual with a tertiary education in STEM, who has some several years of practical experience of software delivery. You might have completed a computer science or mathematics degree, or something similar. As an engineer you're most likely to have studied chemical, process or electrical engineering, maybe even mechanical. Whichever it is, you're a gun at mathematics, coding and problem solving while also known for being methodical, systematic and meticulous.

You can demonstrate some level of experience in most of the following:

 * applied mathematics and statistics
 * software development experience (Python ) and experience with development tools
 * interest in advanced IT topics (eg, simulation, operations research)
 * application of methodical approaches to analysis analytical and problem-solving approach
 * targeted learning involving effective information synthesis and gap analysis
 * highly developed verbal and written communication skills applied to ensure alignment of understanding across multi-disciplinary teams and rapidly further understanding
 * a strong preference to be challenged
 * well-developed collaboration skills to enable desired outcomes within the team as well as independently
 * fluently bi- or multi-lingual

TERMS AND REMUNERATION

Starting salary is negotiated commensurate with the experience you can apply as you start your journey of learning our software and systems. We accommodate flexible hours, within reason (primarily aligned with AEST). Payment is every two weeks.

APPLICATION PROCESS

To be considered, PLEASE FOLLOW THE PROCESS DESCRIBED BELOW.

 * Read the ad fully.
 * Combine into ONE PDF your cover letter and your CV. Tell us why you fit with us. No more than 4 pages total please.
 * Send your application to recruit@paradyn.com.au with subject reference IND-TDT-[Insert Your LastName]

Those who are shortlisted will be contacted. We're grateful for your interest in Paradyn Systems www.paradynsystems.com

It’s that simple. ALDI Good Different.


Job Description


Grow your career with a global retailer as an Analyst within our Data Analytics team at ALDI Australia, based in Minchinbury. This is a full-time permanent position.

You be will responsible for the portfolio management, communication and stakeholder engagement of all Data and Analytics workstreams, as the conduit between the recently created International Data and Analytics domain and ALDI Australia.

This international engagement role will serve as the single point of all global communications and engagement for IDA initiatives within ALDI Australia, requiring exceptional written and verbal communication, with the ability to translate, educate, collaborate and govern the Data & Analytics concept between national and global audiences.

What does the role look like?

 * Serve as the Engagement Lead and single point of communications for all IDA workstreams, between national and international C-Suite stakeholders, driving commercially profitable execution of IDA workstreams across AUS business domains
 * Portfolio Management of all NDA capabilities, including design and implementation of future-state NDA roles & responsibilities governance, ways-of-working frameworks, and capability development beyond current Business Intelligence team structure.
 * AUS change enablement lead for all IDA projects + workstreams across all business domains
 * Provide Use Case Benefit assessments and evaluations, to quantify the value of potential or current IDA use cases across domains; leading to clear prioritisation of workstreams and future data & analytical opportunities within AUS
 * Engage and represent all major AUS DA needs to IDA, to ensure appropriate governance, technology, personnel and workstream architecture is provided to AUS Domains.
 * Grow and develop AUS domain understanding, comprehension and overall DA literacy through education, presentations and training
 * Presenting clear summary of IDA initiatives and implications to C-Suite, for the purpose of informed, educated and harmonised decision-making within / across countries


Qualifications


What do we need from you?

 * Bachelor’s Degree in a relevant field
 * Demonstrated experience in business partnering / consultancy / stakeholder engagement
 * Proven history in presenting to C-Suite Management, being able to translate technical concepts into non-technical language for decision-making purposes
 * Significant exposure to data and analytical techniques, technologies, and projects being rolled out across multiple business domains
 * Capacity for steep learning curve in new DA concepts and architectural requirements
 * Proven history of critical thinking / problem solving capabilities
 * Exceptional communication and presentation skills; including written, spoken and advanced MS Power Point skills, providing the ability to engage C-Suite
 * Change Management and Influencing skills required


Additional Information


What’s in it for you?

We're a team of global innovators, who cherish diverse perspectives that fuel our mission; to simplify the world of work for SMBs worldwide.

If you're looking for a dynamic role where you can unleash your analytical skills and contribute to the growth of a company, then we have the perfect opportunity for you!



As our Data Analyst, you’ll be:

 * Conducting ad hoc analyses: Dive deep into data to address specific questions and investigate important issues that drive decision-making and strategic initiatives.

 * 

What will you bring?

✔️ Experienced - you have 3+ years of experience in a similar role within the SaaS industry or a Scale-up/start-up environment, project managing and delivering high-quality analytics projects to a deadline.

✔️ You will possess strong communication skills, not only in conveying complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders, including executives and other business leaders but also in effectively using data visualisation tools like Tableau (preferable) and Sisense to captivate and engage stakeholders.

✔️ Proficient in SQL (preferably PostgreSQL): Extract, manipulate, and analyse data from relational databases, enabling you to unlock its potential and uncover meaningful insights.

✔️ Strong business acumen: Identify opportunities where data-driven insights can add value and help drive strategic business decisions.

✔️ Excellent communication skills: Translate complex technical concepts into simple language, enabling you to effectively communicate with non-technical stakeholders, including executives and business leaders.

✔️ Meticulous attention to detail: Ensure the accuracy, completeness, and consistency of your data analysis, leaving no stone unturned.

✔️ Have full unrestricted working rights in Australia.



Bonus Points:

Familiarity with version control workflow (Git) and data transformation tool (we use dbt) is highly desirable

It would be highly advantageous if you have previous experience working with Sales and Marketing / GTM SaaS metrics such as MQL, SQL, SAO, ARR, Close Rates, as is experience working with CX metrics such as NPS, CSAT, and Financial/Cost-related metrics.

Experience with programming languages like Python or R: Leverage your programming skills to manipulate and analyse data efficiently, taking your analysis to the next level.

If you live in Australia or New Zealand, you’ve likely heard of AMP. But at a time when society is changing, we are too. We’re now a nimbler business with new leadership and thinking.

Help people create their tomorrow, while you create yours

If we do our job well, we genuinely add to the prosperity of our country and its people.




How you’ll make an impact

You’ll thrive here if…

If you can adapt from BAU to the ambiguous with ease, you’ll do well here. Change is never easy, so bring your commitment, grit and growth mindset.

Because we run lean, you’ll be expected to jump in and deliver across a variety of areas. Meaning, you’ll be closer to the action and executive decisions that influence where we go next.

If you’re someone that can hold their own, you’ll find AMP quite liberating.




Why we think you’ll love working at AMP

Doing what we’ve always done is not an option, so your clever ideas will get airtime here. You’ll be encouraged to speak up and try new things. If they don’t work, we move on – better for it.

We know there’s no one way of doing things. So, you won’t have to sacrifice who you are or how you work to fit in here. We’re inclusive and flexible in many of the ways you’d expect. And in some of the ways you wouldn’t. As long as your health and wellbeing come first - at home and at work.




In fact, most of what makes AMP such a welcoming, enjoyable place to work are our people. Wherever you go, you’ll find moments to connect, feel valued and do meaningful work.




Whether it’s through our first-class leaders who are invested in you and your success. Through year-round opportunities to volunteer, fundraise and give back to the community. Or in the everyday challenges you face as we work together to strengthen this great organisation. Challenges that will stretch you, amplify your potential and compound the impact you have.




We believe in the power of inclusion and diversity

We’re dedicated to fostering inclusion, diversity, and a warm feeling of belonging at AMP. It sparks creativity, ignites innovation, and turns up the dial on the quality of our decisions and performance. This not only makes our workplace more engaged, but also leads to better connections with our customers.

We're also committed to enhancing employment opportunities for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, so we enthusiastically encourage candidates from these backgrounds to apply and explore our Reconciliation Plan on our website here




Ready to create your tomorrow?

If you’re someone who sees opportunity where others see challenge, come and work with us in smart, progressive ways as we transform an iconic Australian brand for the future. And, through a series of career-defining moments, create your own tomorrow.

job_title: Aps5 & Aps6 - Data Analyst, Research, Data And Strategy
job_description:
Contact Officer:


Marcia Keegan on 02 6136 7973, Marcia.KEEGAN@infrastructure.gov.au



Closing Date:


11.59pm AEDT, Monday 26 February 2024.





Our Department Values

Our values set the direction for what it means to work in our department. They inform the standard and expectations of behaviours, skills and capabilities and the attributes we currently have, will continually work to achieve and develop, and that we use to acknowledge and attract, retain and recruit into our department.






The department supports workplace diversity and values the contribution of people from diverse backgrounds. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander peoples, people with disability, people with cultural and linguistic diversity, and LGBTIQ people. The department is committed to achieving gender equality and, in particular, supporting women’s progression into senior leadership.





A LITTLE BIT ABOUT BITRE/BCARR

The Research, Data and Strategy Division strives to strengthen the Department’s strategic policy capabilities. The Division’s work is aimed at assisting in areas such as economic policy, transport and infrastructure and research and data strategy.




The Division includes the Bureau of Infrastructure and Transport Research Economics (BITRE) who provide economic and statistical analysis and applied research on topics including infrastructure, air, water and surface transport, regional and urban matters.




BITRE and BCARR are powered by talented data scientists, economists, engineers, analysts and researchers and provides a dynamic and supportive work environment with an emphasis on learning and development, with opportunities for mentorship by policy, data and research experts.


THE OPPORTUNITIES WE HAVE AVAILABLE

We have several APS5 and APS6 roles available across BITRE in the following research areas:




The Aviation Statistics team work with airlines, aircraft operators and airline data to develop statistical data and publications, supporting the policy and research work of the Department, portfolio agencies, the aviation industry and sharing data with the general public. The team collates and analyses information relating to international, domestic and general aviation aircraft activity, domestic on–time performance, airport traffic and domestic airfare indexes for public release and to support policy development.




The Urban Research team focuses on Australian cities and significant urban areas. The team researches issues affecting Australia’s urban areas and produces research reports and data products to support policy analysis for urban areas.




The Infrastructure and Surface Transport Statistics team produces statistics on maritime and rail transport and infrastructure expenditure, as well as compiling the annual Australian Infrastructure and Transport Statistics Yearbook. Our statistics are compiled primarily using data from industry, and are used to support infrastructure and transport policy and programs, including within the Department by the Surface Transport Emissions and Policy Division and the Infrastructure Divisions.




The Transport Modelling and Research section produces road transport-related statistics and undertakes research into the drivers of current Australian transport activity, the likely future outlook for the domestic transport sector, and the performance of Australia’s current transport infrastructure and likely future infrastructure investment needs. The section also provides data and analytical support to other areas of the Department.




We are offering new roles where people will have opportunities to shine, shaping government policy through the development of data solutions for transport, infrastructure, cities, and regions.




We are seeking candidates who can work both independently and within a team with the ability to make decisions using sound judgement, expertise and knowledge. We are seeking people to fill either APS 5 and APS 6 vacancies, with the position offered based on the type and length of experience relevant to the role. As a rough guide, the APS5 role will be suitable for a person with 1-3 years of data collection/analysis experience and the APS6 role would be suitable for a person with a minimum of 2-3 years of data collection/analysis experience. We will develop a merit list from this round to fill future vacancies across BITRE.




To thrive and be successful in our busy work environment, you will be able to:

 * Achieve results and quality outcomes through demonstrated strong organisational and time management skills and well-developed conceptual and analytical skills. Intermediate or advanced Excel skills, and experience with PowerBI, SAS, R, Python, SQL or similar software in a data analysis capacity will position you well to succeed in these roles.
 * Communicate effectively both in writing and orally, delivering information in a variety of formats for a range of audiences.
 * Collaborate with a diverse range of stakeholders to negotiate positive and productive outcomes.
 * Think strategically, evaluating complex information from a variety of sources to produce accurate reports, briefs and publications that address the needs of target audiences.


WHO ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

The Successful candidate will, under limited direction:








APS5


APS6



Data collection


Apply technical expertise to support data gathering and analysis in transport, cities and regional statistics


Develop subject matter expertise in one or more areas of transport, cities and regional statistics



Analysis


Undertake routine and moderately complex quantitative and statistical analysis


Undertake routine and complex quantitative and statistical analysis



Data management


Effectively navigate database software to update data sets and run data queries


Effectively navigate database software to update data sets and run data queries



Reporting


With limited supervision, produce accurate reports, briefs and publications that address the needs of target audiences


Independently produce accurate reports, briefs and publications that address the needs of target audiences



Respond to data requests


Design and produce quick, accurate ad-hoc retrievals from data sets, to provide relevant outputs to internal and external clients


Design and produce quick, accurate ad-hoc retrievals from data sets, to provide relevant outputs to internal and external clients



Stakeholder relationships


Liaise with internal and external stakeholders to ensure accurate and timely reporting and to support innovation of new datasets and publications


Manage relationships with stakeholder to achieve work area and agency goals to ensure accurate and timely reporting and to support innovation of new datasets and publications.



Innovation


Apply innovative initiatives and contribute to change and to the improvement in quality and efficiency of services


Propose and facilitate innovation initiatives and contribute to business improvement strategies and change in the workplace





The positions would suit individuals with educational qualifications in a relevant field, such as economics, commerce, data science, computer science, information technology, mathematics, statistics or a related field of science or social science.


WHAT ELSE CAN WE OFFER?

Eligibility requirements
Employment with the Department of Infrastructure, Transport, Regional Development, Communications and the Arts is subject to conditions prescribed within the Public Service Act 1999 including:

 * Citizenship: candidates must be an Australian citizen to be eligible for employment with the department.
 * Health Assessment: the preferred candidate may be required to undergo a medical examination conducted by the department’s preferred medical provider.
 * Security Clearance: the successful candidate must be able to obtain and/or maintain a security clearance at Base line vetting. You must be willing to disclose all relevant and required information. You must have lived in Australia, or have a checkable background, for at least the preceding five years for Baseline Vetting clearances. More information on the security clearance vetting process is available on the Australian Government Security Vetting Agency (AGSVA) website.




How to apply
Applications for this opportunity close at 11.59pm AEDT, Monday 26 February 2024.




In applying for this position, you are not required to address individual selection criteria. Rather, you should provide a statement of no more than 2 pages outlining your background, capabilities and experiences, and how these align with the advertised role. You should also provide a CV, no more than 2 pages. The capabilities and behaviours required to be successful for this role are identified in the ‘Who are we looking for’ section. If you have a particular interest in working for a specific team in BITRE/BCARR, please discuss this and why your skills would be suited to this team and/or why this team appeals to you.




Your application should be received through the department’s online recruitment system. Applications via Indeed will not be accepted.




If you experience any issues with the system please contact the recruitment team on 02 6274 6161 or via email at recruitment@infrastructure.gov.au to discuss an alternative way to submit your application.




Please advise the contact officer if you require reasonable adjustments throughout the recruitment process. The department is committed to the accessibility of our systems. If you find accessibility limitations in our systems, please contact recruitment@infrastructure.gov.au and an alternative application format will be provided to you.




Work with us. Apply now!

Responsibilities
About TikTok
TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo.

Why Join Us
Creation is the core of TikTok's purpose. Our platform is built to help imaginations thrive. This is doubly true of the teams that make TikTok possible.
Together, we inspire creativity and bring joy - a mission we all believe in and aim towards achieving every day.
To us, every challenge, no matter how difficult, is an opportunity; to learn, to innovate, and to grow as one team. Status quo? Never. Courage? Always.
At TikTok, we create together and grow together. That's how we drive impact - for ourselves, our company, and the communities we serve.

About the Team
The Product Data Analytics Team analyses a combination of product usage and product performance data to derive meaningful insights that would serve as a guide to better product and decision making for our business leaders. The team will work through different business scenarios including improving Live app Experiences, Host Operation, User experiences. In addition, it is important to manage the data life cycle to ensure problems are quantitatively measured to propose logical solutions.

Responsibilities:

 * Responsible for the data analytics work in international LIVE business, including but not limited to live gifts, host interaction, strategies, enhancing the live streaming revenue.
 * Identify and analyse key factors driving the growth of international LIVE, and propose enhancement plans with logical data support
 * Responsible for the design and analysis of A/B experiments, product iteration impact evaluation, marketing campaign analysis, key metrics trend analysis, etc
 * Work with cross functional partners like Product Managers, Operations, R&D for product optimisation plans and boost business growth
 * Perform market activity analysis and any other analytics that would help guide product and business in decision making.

Qualifications
1. Bachelor degree or above in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics or other related majors;
2. At least 3 years of experiences and above; Experience in supporting analytical work of internet or large scale C2C products is preferred;
3. Proficient in SQL, skilled use of visualisation tools
4. Experience in data extraction, analysis and visualisation in a complex data environment, and have experiences in data landing to the business
5. Excellent communication skills with ability to communicate conclusions effectively to both technical and non-technical audiences, and good analysis report writing ability;
6. Strong learning ability and curiosity driven mindset, independent and possess collaborative problem solving skills

TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.

In the spirit of reconciliation, TikTok acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their Elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.

Austin Health is the major provider of tertiary health services, health professional education and research across 3 campuses in the northeast of Melbourne and state-wide. Austin Health is world-renowned for its research and specialist work in cancer, liver transplantation, spinal cord injuries, neurology, enadocrinology, mental health and rehabilitation.




An exciting opportunity currently exists for an enthusiastic and highly experienced Data Analyst to join our Performance Reporting and Decision Support Department. This is a full time, fixed term (12 month) position.




The Performance Reporting and Decision Support (PRDS) department is responsible for five key areas:

 * Clinical Reporting & Analytics
 * Corporate Reporting
 * Health Information Services (HIS)
 * Data Warehouse Management & Research Analytics
 * Health Information, Reporting & Analytical Projects

Clinical Reporting covers all analytical and reporting services for Austin Health in relation to clinical operations. Corporate Reporting oversees clinical costing, funding analytics and corporate reporting. The PRDS division is also responsible for the Austin data warehouses and provision of data to the organisation.

HIS consists of medical record scanning, casemix/coding services, submissions of external mandatory activity reporting, corporate records management, morbidity data collection and release of patient information including Freedom of Information.

The PRDS division has a staffing of approximately 70 EFT located over three sites.

Key responsibilities will include:

This role is responsible for supporting Austin Health with their reporting and analytical needs. The Data Analyst will be customer focused and actively engage with all levels of clinical and non-clinical staff.

The role will require a detailed understanding of systems, data and information relevant to each clinical or operational area supported and be comfortable providing the business with pro-active, value added insights. You will work with the organisation to deliver key reports and insights to assist in improving effectiveness and efficiency and to assist the organisation to deliver efficient and safe patient care.

A client-focused approach is essential to this role and a willingness to engage that involves getting out amongst the business and being a part of their discussions and strategic planning. Working collaboratively within a team of analysts and business partners is essential.

To be successful in this role you must demonstrate:

 * Analytical & problem-solving skills with good attention to detail
 * Strong SQL programming skills with demonstrated experience in building complex queries

 * Strong knowledge with using business intelligence tools and concepts
 * Experience in working with large complex data sets

 * Experience in health sector reporting
 * Ability to work independently and within a team environment
 * Good organisational, time management, written and verbal skills

Desirable but not essential:

 * Tertiary qualifications in Business, Information Technology, Statistics and/or Data Science
 * Experience in using R and/or Python for undertaking data analysis
 * Previous experience in the public health sector

Work with us! Your reward is to work in a collaborative environment which will provide you with opportunities for ongoing training and development. Your benefits will include salary packaging, and employee assistance program.

All appointments are made subject to a satisfactory National Police Check conducted by Austin Health and if required, a Working With Children Check.

Austin Health is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to attracting and retaining a diverse workforce that reflects the community we serve. Applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders are encouraged.

job_description:
* You are a problem solver with a background as a Control Analyst and or Business Analyst.
 * We are one of the best and most advanced Cyber Security teams in Australia.
 * Together we can contribute to protecting the Group, its customers and community.


Your business:

The Technology division delivers the Group's information technology and banking operations functions to ensure the highest levels of customer service through world-class process excellence and technology innovation. Cyber Security protects the bank and our customers from theft, losses and risk events, through effective and proactive management of cyber security, privacy and operational risk,

We support our people with the flexibility to balance where work is done with at least half your time each month connecting in office. We also have many other flexible working options available including changing start and finish times, part-time arrangements and job share to name a few. Talk to us about how these arrangements might work for you.

Your new team:

The Data Access and Behavioural Analytics Team are responsible for the consultation, design, build and operation of group-wide security and identity and access services. The control objective to detect inappropriate access to customer personal information held in CBA applications. This includes;

 * Triage of generated alerts and escalation.
 * Reporting of control performance.
 * Design, build and operation of the UBA control flows.


Your impact and contribution:

As the Control Analyst - Data Access and Behavioural Analytics, you will assist in supporting the design and operating effectiveness of user behaviour analytics controls by using data to drive insights and enhance the cyber control environment.

This role will see you working with various colleagues and stakeholders to scale and manage behavioural analysis capabilities aligned to identity management and ensure that the group can identify potentially suspicious internal inappropriate access to data held in CBA Applications. Your contributions within this role will help ensure that appropriate triage and management strategies are in place to protect the financial wellbeing of our customers and communities.

You will also:

 * Work with the User Behaviour Analytics (UBA) Control Manager, Risk Management, Privacy and Business Unit stakeholders across the group, to ensure that anomalous behaviour is detected in key internally accessible systems, and associated remediation are performed to meet the controls objectives.
 * Ensure continuous improvement of data access anomalous behaviour use cases and processes through the use of automation.
 * Support the regular reporting of key risk indicators and control performance to stakeholder and risk groups.
 * Support the expansion of control coverage to ensure the controls are implemented across high-risk business areas within the core business units and subsidiaries.
 * Build strong relationships with business stakeholders, project teams, and operational teams so that UBA control(s) are actively being used in the business to reduce risk; exceptions captured, actioned or risk accepted.
 * Use data driven insights to develop and enhance use cases that will enable the group to detect suspicious behaviours of staff accessing customer data in applications.
 * Assist with managing the UBA capabilities including the product and product roadmaps to ensure relevant stakeholders (inside Cyber, Business Unit Chief Control Offices, Privacy Enforceable Undertaking Program and key stakeholders) understand the goals and requirements related to control deliverables.


We are interested in people who:

As the Control Analyst you will have an understating of working across a large IT function, supporting the organisation with key requirement and initiates. You understand how to gather requirements and build strong stakeholder relationships to ensure the organisation meets its cyber objectives.

You will bring:

 * The ability to elicit business requirements and comprehend complex business IT processes.
 * An understanding or experience of user behaviour analytics highly desirable.
 * The ability to manage a variety of queries support the manager and wider business.
 * A strong written and verbal communication skills.
 * An analytical approach to problem solving and relish working as part of a collaborative and high-performing team.
 * Experience in working with large volumes of data highly regarded e.g., Excel, Power BI etc.


If this role is of interest to you, please apply directly or reach out to have a confidential discussion in more detail.

job_description:
Positions: Data and Information Analysts (Bulk Round)

Location: Canberra or Sydney

Part-time

Closing Date: 11:30pm, Wednesday 21 February 2024

Contact Officer: Gavin Evans, gavin.evans@aihw.gov.au or 02 6249 4880

More information: Visit our Careers Page and the AIHW Enterprise Agreement

This recruitment exercise may be used to fill similar positions within the Institute over the coming 18 months.



About the AIHW



The Australian Institute of Health and Welfare (AIHW) provides reliable, regular, and relevant information and

statistics on Australia’s health and welfare.

We are committed to providing high quality, national data and analysis across the health, housing, and

community services sectors. This covers a wide range of areas, including health and welfare expenditure,

hospitals, disease and injury, disability, mental health, ageing, disadvantaged and vulnerable populations,

homelessness, and First Nations health and welfare.



The AIHW Difference



The AIHW’s APS Employee Census results attest to our positive and supportive workplace culture. We are an

inclusive, flexible, and productive workplace where people are treated with respect and courtesy, and diverse

and unique attributes are recognised and valued. Our results also show that we achieve top ten rankings in

staff engagement, leadership, communication, innovation, and wellbeing scales out of 101 APS agencies.

We offer a range of benefits including:

 * access to flexible working arrangements to support your work/life balance.

 * attractive remuneration packages including generous superannuation and leave provisions.

 * challenging and fulfilling work where you can use your skills and expertise.

 * opportunities for professional development including study assistance.



We are committed to creating genuine opportunities for everyone and we welcome applications from

Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander people(s), people with disability, LGBTIQA+, neurodivergent people,

and people from diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds.

The AIHW has offices in Canberra and Sydney and offers to work in other locations may be considered.

For more information, visit the Benefits of working for the AIHW page of our website.



Position Summary



We are seeking talented and enthusiastic Data and Information Analysts to perform one or more of the

following roles:

 * Working with data and large databases, including data validation and processing

 * Contribute to the development, documentation, and maintenance of data collections and standards

 * Undertaking research and statistical analysis and interpretation of data

 * Designing, researching, analysing, and presenting information in various formats

 * Providing support with planning, organising, and assisting in projects

 * Manipulating and interrogating databases using a range of software (including SAS, Python, R, and

other software)

 * Liaising and negotiating with internal and external stakeholders including government agencies,

State and Local authorities, and business or community organisations

 * Assisting with website administration and maintenances

 * Drafting papers and reports, including web reports.

The successful applicants will possess an understanding of and skills in, or aptitude for, statistical and

research project work in a range of subject areas. They will also possess verbal and written communication

skills, and sound organisational skills.

We encourage applicants from a wide range of skills and disciplines. This may include (but is not limited to)

those with qualifications or relevant work experience in statistics, epidemiology, demography, science

communication and journalism, database administration, data science, health informatics, economics,

actuarial studies, accounting, health sciences, social sciences, data mining, predictive modelling or

geospatial/GIS (geographic information system) mapping.



Selection Criteria



Our ideal candidate will have most or all of the following skills and knowledge:



1. Good verbal and written communication skills, including the ability to communicate, and to prepare

clear and logical papers, presentations and reports using plain English.

2. Demonstrated numeracy and analytical skills, and experience in using software to process or

present data analysis.

3. Demonstrated organisational skills including the ability to prioritise one’s workload, work within

timeframes, and escalate issues when required.

4. Sound interpersonal skills, including the ability to build and sustain positive working relationships

and contribute to a team.

5. Demonstrated commitment to personal development, including the ability to identify own strengths

and development needs and seek self-development opportunities.

Tertiary qualifications in a relevant health or welfare discipline, or previous experience in a role involving data

management and development, collation, or research analysis and reporting will be highly regarded.



How to Apply

Please submit your application online via the AIHW e-Recruit system. When applying online for the first time,

you will need to register and provide a valid email address.



Your application must include:

1. A summary of your relevant skills and experience and explain why you would be the best person for

the role. Your response should align with the position summary and selection criteria information

above, and must be no more than 750 words.

2. Your current CV and the names of two referees.



Please note, late applications will not be accepted.



Reasonable Adjustment



The AIHW is committed to providing accessible, inclusive, and equitable recruitment processes for all

candidates. If you require a reasonable adjustment (at any stage of the recruitment process), you can note

this in your application and provide details of any adjustments required. All efforts will be made to meet your

requirements.

Reasonable adjustments may include, but are not limited to, additional interview time, being interviewed at a

particular time of day, interview material being printed in large font, and making allowances for varying

communication styles.



RecruitAbility



The AIHW is committed to supporting the employment and career development of people with

disability. Our participation in APS RecruitAbility means we will progress an applicant who declares that they

have disability to a further stage in the recruitment process, where they opt into RecruitAbility on the

application form and meet the minimum requirements for the role.

job_title: Analyst/Senior Analyst, Data Collection Management Team
job_description:
* Contribute to APRA’s role as prudential regulator of financial institutions
 * Play a key role in improving the quality of the data that APRA collects from the financial institutions
 * A highly impactful role working collaboratively across APRA while also engaging with industry and partner agencies, including the Reserve Bank of Australia and Australian Bureau of Statistics
 * Opportunity for flexible working arrangements in a workplace that values diversity, inclusion, and work/life balance
 * Role based out of APRA’s Sydney office.

The Role

APRA’s mandate is to protect the Australian Community by establishing and enforcing prudential standards and practices designed to ensure that, under all reasonable circumstances, financial promises made by institutions we supervise are met within a stable, efficient and competitive financial system.

To help us deliver on our mandate and strategic priorities, we have an opportunity for an Analyst and Senior Analyst to join our Data Collection Management team.
In these roles, you will be involved in the collection and collation of information from our regulated and non-regulated institutions, while ensuring that APRA employees and external stakeholders have access to accurate and up to date data.

Key responsibilities

 * Data Quality Assurance: Collaborate with various users of APRA’s data to maintain data quality standards
 * Stakeholder Transparency: Assist in establishing and maintaining transparency with internal and external stakeholders
 * Data Transformation: Contribute to APRA’s ongoing data transformation program
 * Technical Support: Facilitate the provision of accurate technical advice on reporting queries and issues
 * Relationship Management: Maintain effective contact with APRA’s supervisory teams and financial institutions
 * Effective Time Management: Prioritize day-to-day tasks and ad-hoc duties efficiently.

The Team

The Data Collection Management team is part of APRA’s Technology and Data Division and is responsible for:

 * The collection of data from regulated and non-regulated institutions using APRA’s data collection tools D2A and APRA Connect
 * Acting as the first point of call for industry engagement with regards to the provision of data to APRA
 * Ensuring financial institutions meet their reporting obligations on-time
 * Contributing to the development of actions to effectively monitor and mitigate issues identified.
 * Administering the registration of regulated and non-regulated institutions that provide data to APRA and key Responsible individuals in those organisations.

The ideal candidate will possess experience in:

 * Customer support: Ability to work with a variety of institutions with varying level of technical capabilities to ensure that data is provided to APRA and reporting issues are resolved in a timely manner
 * Service level management: Ensuring that both the industries and APRA commitments are meet in a timely manner. Following up with late reporters
 * Communicating effectively: Excellent written and verbal communication skills for engaging various stakeholders both internally and externally
 * Troubleshooting: Working with the industry and subject matter experts to resolve reporting issues.
 * Legislative Interpretation: Understanding and interpreting reporting standards and legislative requirements.

About APRA

The Australian Prudential Regulation Authority (APRA) places you at the heart of Australia’s financial services industry. APRA serves the Australian community by helping ensure financial institutions deliver on the financial commitments they make, within a stable, efficient and competitive financial system.

At APRA we’re committed to providing an inclusive workplace where everyone belongs, feels valued and respected. We aspire to attract and foster diversity of background, thought, and experience, recognising that a broad range of perspectives, approaches and ideas makes us stronger, and better enables us to meet our obligation to protect the financial wellbeing of the Australian community. When applying, please inform us of any adjustments you may need during the interview process.

* Work-life balance combining Melbourne office-based and work from home
 * Supportive and inclusive workplace fostering strong collaboration
 * Genuine opportunities to grow within the business and shape your future career

job_description:
CEVA Logistics provides global supply chain solutions to connect people, products and providers all around the world. Present in 170 countries and with more than 110,000 employees spread over 1,300 sites, we are well on our way to achieving our vision: to be a Top 5 global 3PL. We believe that our employees are the key to our success. We want to engage and empower our diverse, global team to co-create value with our customers through our solutions in contract logistics and air, ocean, ground, and finished vehicle transport.



YOUR ROLE


As the Transport Management System (TMS) Analyst / Super-User for our NSW Ground Transport network, you’ll drive the effective use, maintenance, and improvement of CEVA's transport systems and will be the go-to subject matter expert, offering training, support, and collaboration to optimise and achieve transport operations excellence.


Whilst this is not an ‘IT’ role, you’ll draw on your operational expertise to identify the optimal TMS configuration to allow operations to deliver operational excellence for CEVA and its customers.


WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?


Specifically, you will:




 * Master the TMS and related platforms, serving as the primary contact for user inquiries
 * Provide effective support, troubleshoot issues, and conduct user training sessions
 * Collaborate with IT for system configurations aligned with business needs
 * Ensure data integrity, generate reports, and contribute to decision-making insights
 * Identify process inefficiencies, proposing system-based solutions.


WHAT ARE WE LOOKING FOR?


Our ideal candidate has operational experience gained in a transport 3PL (preferably transport fleet control / coordination) together with strong functional expertise with transport management systems. You’ll also have:




 * Intermediate-level proficiency in MS Office applications, and proven experience with web-based applications and customised software solutions
 * Strong analytical skillset including proficiency in data analysis and reporting
 * Excellent written and verbal communication skills, and ability to translate technical concepts to a wide audience
 * Flexible and adaptable, given span of hours (and therefore related support required) in our transport operations.


In addition to providing proof of work rights and suitable professional referees, progressed candidates will be required to undergo a medical assessment and national police check.


WHAT DO WE HAVE TO OFFER?


In addition to a challenging and rewarding work environment and competitive compensation, we are proud to offer a range of employee benefits designed to support your wellbeing, and help you thrive at work and in life.




 * Personal wellbeing: prioritise your health and wellbeing through the CEVAwell program, Employee Assistance Program, Volunteer Time Off, and Life & Total Permanent Disability Insurance.
 * Work-life balance: benefit from flexible, hybrid, and remote work options, along with additional paid parental leave for primary carers.
 * Professional development: your growth is essential to us. Unlock your potential through secondment and internal mobility opportunities, study assistance, leadership and mentoring programs, the CMA CGM Learning Academy, early career pathways and more.
 * Financial wellbeing: We care about your financial security. Enjoy exclusive offers and discounts from our partners, novated leasing, annual safety workwear reimbursement, employee referral incentives, service recognition and short-term incentive plans.

As a global organisation, diversity is critical to our business success; only when we can reflect the cultures, languages, attitudes, and local knowledge of our customers, can we succeed. By employing people with different experiences and abilities, we expand our knowledge and increase our creativity and innovation. Your team
The Enterprise Data team enables Great Southern Bank’s business units to make timely, data-driven decisions. We are a team of data and technology specialists that partners with teams from across the organisation to solve business problems and are responsible for governing, growing and maintaining the bank’s Enterprise Data Platforms, Reporting & Analytics systems to deliver accurate, timely information, insights and innovative technology solutions.
You report to the Senior Manager – Insights & Analytics and have a dotted reporting line to the Senior Manager – Remediation.

This is contract position until March 2025 based in the Brisbane office, however for the right candidate this position could also be based in Sydney.

The Role

 * Your role within the Enterprise Data team is to provide dedicated data analysis support to the Remediation team. This will involve you working closely with Remediation analysts and other team members to:
 * Identify customers, products and services impacted by an incident
 * Determine if those customers are eligible for remediation
 * Assist with the development of compensation calculations
 * Create customer payment and communication files to drive compensation and customer contact campaigns
 * Performing, where required, quality assurance activities to ensure accuracy of outcomes


You will leverage all Great Southern Bank data sources, platforms and systems, along with your analytical skills to achieve successful remediation outcomes.
You play a critical role supporting the development and embedment of our customer remediation framework and processes through the creation and execution of bespoke and standardised/repeatable data queries.
You will be flexible and creative to ensure the best data is used in each situation, helping to solve for instances where there might be gaps or ambiguity and always ensuring that the data we use in remediation has been appropriately tested and validated.

Your responsibilities
Analytics & Insights

 * Work with the Remediation team to understand the scope of a remediation activity and the key data sources that are required
 * Build datasets based on business requirements to identify potentially impacted customers, products and transactions and highlight/resolve any gaps or anomalies that you observe
 * Tell stories with data using engaging visualisation, or presentations to communicate your key messages
 * Leverage both structured and unstructured data sources to solve business problems.
 * Ensure timely & accurate delivery of data outputs to enable remediations to be delivered in a fast and efficient manner
 * Contribute to identifying data gaps and potential opportunities for business growth and further exploration.


Stakeholder Engagement

 * You are a trusted advisor and supporter within the Enterprise Data Office and the Remediation Team.
 * You engage in discovery processes with key stakeholders to really understand their business problems and determine the areas of key analysis and insight investigation.
 * You proactively manage stakeholder expectations through thoughtful planning and regular showcasing of outcomes.
 * You conduct analysis or build data products to help your stakeholders solve problems through data and provide consultative support to guide them on how to use insights or data products to help make business decisions.
 * Maintaining the data environment
 * You work with data engineers to help map, validate, and document data transformation between data layers, and perform user acceptance testing on the data products.
 * You use your strong attention to detail to validate the quality of the data you use for your business recommendations, provide input to uplift and help communicate any issues to those impacted.
 * You liaise with Data Stewards to ensure data quality and consistency and support them in finding root cause of quality issues.
 * You make recommendations on how to consolidate data definitions or improve efficiencies and reusability within the data landscape, including consolidating dashboards or data products.


Risk Management

 * Manage and implement a prudent risk management approach in all aspects of your team.
 * Report and record all risks, hazards and incidents in line with our Risk Management framework and our Risk Appetite Statement.
 * Implement and monitor the Great Southern Bank risk management process to eliminate or minimise WHS hazards and risks where appropriate and manage and respond to any hazards/incidents raised by your team.


Your experience

 * Ideally, you will have been in an analytics role for 2+ years with the following exposure:
 * 1+ years proven experience in performing data analysis in customer remediation projects (essential).
 * Proven experience partnering with business stakeholders, building strong relationships & creating trust through delivering analytical outcomes.
 * Consultative approach. You are not afraid to challenge stakeholder needs and interpret what they are really trying to ask for.
 * Advanced Experience with SAS and SQL to solve for analytical business problems.
 * Experience with relevant programming languages (e.g. SAS, SQL, AWS, Databricks, Python, R, Scala, etc.).
 * 2+ years’ experience in the banking and financial services industry (highly desirable).
 * Experience with data visualisation tools (such as Tableau / Power BI).
 * Proven understanding of ETL Systems and processes, ideally on a cloud data platform.
 * Proven experience working with raw and complex data.
 * Experience contributing to building data marts or data modelling for an organisation (desirable).
 * In-depth consumer banking product knowledge (desirable).


Your qualifications

Our Research Analysts (RAs) are involved in diverse, challenging assignments within a stimulating, collegial work environment. You’ll work side by side with internationally recognised experts in financial economics, corporate finance, energy, competition, and regulatory economics. You’ll have the opportunity to support our Principals and Academic Advisors as they serve as expert witnesses before courts and arbitration panels on behalf of some of the world’s largest and most successful law firms and corporations, in addition to numerous public and government agencies across the globe.

As an RA, you’ll participate in project teams with senior consulting staff. The RA role includes analysis, modelling, and research functions on client projects. Major focus areas for new RAs can be financial and economic modelling, industry analyses, and literature review.

A typical day for an RA includes:

 * Combining economic theory and industry knowledge to solve real problems
 * Using statistical analyses to extract information from messy data
 * Constructing models from a blend of theoretical concepts to answer complex questions
 * Reviewing literature and industry trends to understand the debate around key developments

The ideal Research Analyst has an Honours degree or three-year Bachelor’s degree with an excellent academic record (Distinction on average) in economics, finance, or other quantitative subjects. Most importantly, Brattle RAs are looking to continuously learn and take ownership of their work.

We are currently accepting applications for RAs who can join our Sydney office Graduate Program beginning January 2025.

The Cancer Institute is a collaborative working environment that encourages diversity and inclusion in how we work and the way we work together. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples are strongly encouraged to apply. Greater consideration will be given to suitable applicants, in order to improve access to employment and career opportunities (GSE Rule 26).




What you will be doing

You will have demonstrated experience in developing and maintaining data architecture, using Microsoft developer and data management tools including Microsoft SQL Server and SSIS to aid in the provision and improvement of cancer screening services in NSW and support the achievement of Cancer Plan objectives.

This is a multifaceted role providing business and technical knowledge to assist the Senior Data Analyst inform management in decision making. The role includes assisting in integrating user feedback, policy changes, evolving business needs, system upgrades and schema/ETL changes into the Screening and Prevention data architecture.




For your application to be considered

To submit your application, please provide:

 * Your resume (maximum five pages).
 * A covering letter addressing the Essential Requirements, as outlined below.
 * A response to the Pre-screening Questions, as outlined below.




Essential requirements

 * Tertiary qualifications in information technology or engineering, or a related discipline; or demonstrated equivalent professional experience.
 * Experience with SQL Server and Microsoft SSIS in database development and administration.
 * Understanding of data management and governance principles and methods as they relate to health records.
 * Experience with undertaking data analysis and reporting on large datasets for the purpose of performance monitoring and improvement.
 * Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively as part of a team, and independently with minimal supervision.
 * Understanding of and commitment to comply with relevant confidentiality and privacy guidelines.




Pre-screening questions

 * Please outline your experience and what your role was in any data remediation/management project or activity?

 * Please outline your experience and what your role was in any data warehousing activity.

Interested?

How you’ll make an impact

The purpose of this role is to support the Head of Risk & Control and Senior Manager, Risk and Control, and is an integral part of the First Line Risk and Compliance team. This team provides thought leadership advising on the management of related risks and controls; compliance and issue, incident and breach monitoring; the oversight of the internal customer resolution function; and for providing governance and reporting. It requires working closely with key stakeholders and senior business representatives and supporting them in their efforts to improve and enhance the operating control environment, embed new law and develop efficiencies by providing business focussed, timely, proactive and solutions orientated compliance advice and insight across a range of areas.

Main Focus Areas:

This role will focus on supporting the management of the end-to-end risk and control environment for the Super and Retirement Division. To achieve this outcome, you are responsible for building strong relationships with key stakeholders. You will be expected to provide risk support in relation to the identification, assessment, and management of risk and drive a strong risk culture that helps achieve business objectives.

Overall Responsibility

 * Working with Senior Manager, Risk and Controls to implement, maintain and coordinate reviews of First Line Risk Management governance frameworks, ensuring that they are operating effectively within the wider AMP Group frameworks.
 * Support the Head of Risk and Compliance and Senior Manager, Risk and Controls in the oversight of the E2E control environment across other relevant business functions.

Reporting and Governance

 * Work with Senior Manager, Risk and Controls in developing management information (MI) and track progress and managing insight driven reporting and governance function;
 * Support Senior Manager, Risk and Controls in Risk Profile and Risk reports for risk committees, EXCO and Boards (where required);
 * Support Senior Manager, Risk and Controls in the analysis and interpretation of key risk indicators results to identify systemic issues for escalation and investigation;
 * Support the Senior Manager, Risk and Controls in regularly reviewing the risk management and controls frameworks to ensure they continue to be effective for the management of risk;

Control Assurance

 * Support ad-hoc reviews of areas of risk as well as the definition of control uplifts through the transformation;
 * Support the coordination of Controls Assurance related initiatives across people, processes and systems as requested by Heads Of Risk and Compliance;
 * Review and assess control test plans and methodologies for controls with consideration of the business operations, processes, and risks.
 * Support Senior Manager, Risk and Controls in the review of events for lessons learnt, including identification of systemic issues across different processes / business lines etc for reporting to Director, Advice.
 * Documentation and reporting of work through GRC and appropriate governance;
 * Ensuring implementation and continual improvement of processes to proactively manage to new SBR requirements;

What you will bring to the team

Ideally, you will bring the following experiences to this role:

 * Analyst, Controls Assurance is expected to have competencies for the role and experience (3-5 yrs) in financial services and/or assurance knowledge in order to effectively and efficiently design and execute controls testing plans
 * Financial Services experience in Audit practice or industry (desirable)
 * Relevant industry and other professional qualifications
 * Tertiary qualifications in a business-related discipline (desirable)
 * Strong understanding and experience within financial services industry and current and proposed financial services regulatory and legislative requirements.
 * Experience working on projects to deliver key business outcome.
 * Proven customer service orientation.
 * Proven ability to manage change effectively
 * Previous experience in operating in a 3LOD environment would be highly desirable.
 * Data analytics skills and experience in the use of reporting software
 * Experience in business and management reporting
 * Track record of driving efficient and effective operational processes
 * Demonstrated engagement within a matrixed corporate organisation
 * Ability to operate in a business environment through change

You’ll thrive here if…

If you can adapt from BAU to the ambiguous with ease, you’ll do well here. Change is never easy, so bring your commitment, grit and growth mindset.

Because we run lean, you’ll be expected to jump in and deliver across a variety of areas. Meaning, you’ll be closer to the action and executive decisions that influence where we go next.

If you’re someone that can hold their own, you’ll find AMP quite liberating.

Why we think you’ll love working at AMP

Doing what we’ve always done is not an option, so your clever ideas will get airtime here. You’ll be encouraged to speak up and try new things. If they don’t work, we move on – better for it.

We know there’s no one way of doing things. So, you won’t have to sacrifice who you are or how you work to fit in here. We’re inclusive and flexible in many of the ways you’d expect. And in some of the ways you wouldn’t. As long as your health and wellbeing come first - at home and at work.

In fact, most of what makes AMP such a welcoming, enjoyable place to work are our people. Wherever you go, you’ll find moments to connect, feel valued and do meaningful work.

Whether it’s through our first-class leaders who are invested in you and your success. Through year-round opportunities to volunteer, fundraise and give back to the community. Or in the everyday challenges you face as we work together to strengthen this great organisation. Challenges that will stretch you, amplify your potential and compound the impact you have.

We believe in the power of inclusion and diversity

We’re dedicated to fostering inclusion, diversity, and a warm feeling of belonging at AMP. It sparks creativity, ignites innovation, and turns up the dial on the quality of our decisions and performance. This not only makes our workplace more engaged, but also leads to better connections with our customers.

We're your allies in the search for the perfect fit - when you apply, let us know how we can support you to put your best self forward during our selection process.

We're also committed to enhancing employment opportunities for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, so we enthusiastically encourage candidates from these backgrounds to apply and explore our Reconciliation Plan on our website> (insert link)

Ready to create your tomorrow?

If you’re someone who sees opportunity where others see challenge, come and work with us in smart, progressive ways as we transform an iconic Australian brand for the future. And, through a series of career-defining moments, create your own tomorrow.

Don’t procrastinate! We review applications when we get them, and if we discover the ideal candidate, we may close the role earlier than the advertised close date.

Looking forward to meeting you.

 * Bachelor’s degree AND 2 years of business experience, with a strong technology understanding OR 5 years of experience without a degree.
 * Experience working with EDI
 * Project Management and client relationship experience
 * Strong oral and written communication and interpersonal skills

What experience is preferred?




 * Supply chain management experience

*EOE including disability/ veteran*

What’s the role?

As a Senior Data/Insights Analyst in the Consumer Growth team, your role will be pivotal in providing data-driven decision-making by uncovering insights from diverse data sources. You will fuel strategic and operational initiatives that generate incremental performance improvement across revenue, productivity, costs and our Consumer’s experiences. You will achieve this by becoming a domain expert in the company’s data capability and responsible for its exploitation across the Consumer organisation.

What you’ll do:

 * Be part of creating an insights rich Enterprise Consumer Data asset
   
   

 * Design & build sophisticated end-to-end consumer data models

 * Work closely with the wider Consumer Growth team, product owners and internal stakeholders to understand their data requirements

 * Drive new and creative ways to leverage consumer data to provide descriptive and prescriptive insights that will direct optimal courses of action

 * Provide ongoing support to the business to ensure that the consumer data solutions are being used efficiently and effectively

 * Identifying opportunities for continuously improving the consumer data program via new sources, methods and views

Who are you?

 * Ability to work across large transactional datasets (Big Data), with desirable experience with population oriented data (BigQuery, Spark, Redshift, Hadoop and others).
   
   

 * Advanced SQL and data transformation experience

 * Ability to plan and execute sophisticated multi-source and multi-dimensional streams

 * Sound problem solving skills

About Single Digital Patient Record (SDPR)

Working at eHealth NSW is more than a job. Every day, we set out to design, build and innovate world class digital solutions that will transform how healthcare is delivered to patients across NSW.

The Single Digital Patient Record (SDPR) program will provide a highly secure, holistic and integrated view of the care a patient receives across the New South Wales (NSW) public health system. It will transform the digital systems that NSW’s public healthcare workers use every day to deliver care.

The SDPR is a next generation integrated electronic medical record (eMR), laboratory information management system (LIMS) and patient administration system (PAS). The program will replace the current nine eMRs, 10 PAS and five pathology LIMS in use across NSW Health.

SDPR will be delivered across NSW Health through a partnership between Local Health Districts (LHDs), Specialty Health Networks (SHNs), eHealth NSW, NSW Health Pathology and other agencies.

Visit our SDPR Careers Page to access vacancies across the program.



Come work with us

We currently have multiple exciting opportunities in the Single Digital Patient Record program within eHealth NSW Program Delivery Directorate for Data Courier Analysts.

Reporting into the Solution Architecture and Technical Analysis Capability Manager you will be responsible for the migration of configuration data between Electronic Medical Record (EMR) environments, ensuring data integrity, and adhering to organisational and compliance standards. Working closely and collaborating with IT professionals, and clinical teams, you will ensure a seamless transition of system configurations.

Your role will sit amongst peers in the Solution Architecture and Technical Analysis team. In addition to working on some of NSW Health’s most transformative digital projects, you will also support the ongoing development of best practice methodologies, including contributing to the establishment of a centre of excellence for this discipline, for the benefit of eHealth NSW more broadly.

Health Manager Level 3, commencing salary from $122,850 - $139,559 per annum plus 11% superannuation.


For more information, read the full Position Description.


What you will do



As an integral member of the Solution Architecture and Technical Analysis team, you will:

 * Configure, administer, and support the system interfaces and data courier tools used for the migration of configuration data between EMR environments.
 * Monitor configuration data transfers between environments, troubleshoot and resolve issues, and ensure timely completion of data migrations and integrity of data transferred.
 * Ensure that batch migrations are conducted seamlessly and oversee the scheduled transfers minimising disruptions.
 * Work closely with IT teams, and clinical departments to ensure that migrations align with organisational needs and clinical workflows.
 * Maintain detailed logs and histories of all migrations, ensuring full compliance with organisational standards and regulations.
 * Generate and present reports detailing migration activities, successes, challenges, and recommendations.
 * Stay updated with the latest developments in the data transfer tools and recommend improvements or modifications to optimise the data migration process.
 * Provide training and guidance on Data Courier processes to other team members and offer support during migration processes.



About you




The skills, knowledge and experience we are looking for in you are:

 * A degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Healthcare Administration or relevant field, or equivalent work experience, or a combination of study and work experience.
 * Proven experience in a similar role within a large organisation, with a demonstrated understanding of EMR systems and the criticality of ensuring data integrity.
 * Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work collaboratively in a team-oriented environment.

job_title: Big Data Intern (Data Processing And Analytics)
job_description:
We are inviting selected students (BA, MS) in Data Science to be part of pioneering the cloud, data, AI and web3 space. You will have the opportunity to contribute to the development of one of the world's first large-scale open data clouds and analytics engines. Openmesh is a dedicated global initiative that brings together brilliant minds in the tech industry to create open data and open infrastructures that will be pivotal in shaping the next 10-20 years.

This internship can be used for your 400 hours of industry experience (PEP 40). This is a 2-12 weeks paid internship to begin soon. The role will take place in our Sydney George St. Office. Unlock your career potential by working with a world class team, opportunity for permanent job placements, competitive salaries, and exciting cash prize competitions!

About Openmesh and Xnode

Today a handful of corporations control 90% of the world's data and IT infrastructure and we are expected to trust them. This is not just bad for business; it's bad for everyone. Information asymmetry has led to social inequality, scandals, polarization, and corruption. Sometimes, it has even led to war. Centralized data control acts as a potential chokepoint for innovation, raises privacy concerns, and creates a bottleneck for the free flow of data.

Openmesh is a cutting-edge new open-source cloud infrastructure and a global open data network aimed at storing important global data without a middleman. It is the largest open web3 data lake, covering approximately 80% of the entire crypto and web3 ecosystem today. In 2023 and 2024, we aim to expand our data coverage to include public health and scientific research data.

Openmesh enables anyone to create their own decentralized data cloud, connect globally, share data securely, slash deployment costs, and automate data cloud setup. The Openmesh Network is designed to collect, store, process, stream, and provide data connectivity for anyone, anywhere, anytime, without the need for registration, licensing, or payments. Think of Openmesh as the internet's open data fabric. It grants universal access and prevents interferences created by regulators, governments, corporations, and even its own creators. The possibilities are endless.

Core Products

Our flagship product, Xnode, is an integral part of this vision, offering a revolutionary platform for developers to build decentralized data clouds. Xnode, enables developers to build their own decentralized data clouds with data connectivity, data APIs, and query & analytics engines in mere minutes, instead of weeks or months. They pay only for computing and storage, sidestepping licensing and setup fees. Xnode facilitates a 10-15 fold cost reduction in running and operating data clouds and can save over 95% of deployment time.

Pythia is a powerhouse analytics & query engine that transforms raw data into actionable insights. Pythia allows anyone to design, build, visualize, and deploy powerful data products.

Unified APIs provide a single endpoint for all crypto & web3 data, making it accessible to anyone, anywhere, without any costs. There are no licenses, registrations, or setup fees involved.

Our vision

Our vision is to democratize data and address information asymmetry at a scale. Data & information is the most valuable commodity in the world. Without quality, reliable data, all webpages, apps, and the entire internet will stop working. We believe access to reliable, unedited information is a fundamental right- an aspect of a free and democratic society. The Core Principles of Openmesh, by design, has no single authority that can alter its data, how the information is distributed or controlled, or who can see what and when. The infrastructure and entire technology stack is open-source and governed by an open-source community.

The opportunity

Leverage this paid internship opportunity to fulfill your PEP 40H industry experience requirement.

You have the option to work in person or remotely. There is an upcoming hackathon on the 28th.

   Career Progression - top-performing candidates will receive a full-time offer.

 * 
 * The specialized knowledge and skills you gain through the program will prepare you for a successful career at Openmesh.

Why Join Us

 * Lead a revolutionary product that is reshaping the landscape of data management and accessibility.
 * Collaborate with a global community of innovators and thought leaders in the decentralized space.
 * Make a significant impact on how data is accessed and utilized worldwide, promoting transparency, efficiency, and democratization.

job_description:
An ideal opportunity to get a step into the world of Financial Risk and Modelling.




 * A tertiary qualification in Banking and Finance, Risk Management, or a quantitative discipline such as Engineering, Mathematics, or Actuarial Science

 * Strong verbal and written communication skills
