Role Purpose

Wood Mackenzie Power and Renewables provides a one-stop integrated subscription, analysis and advisory service for companies in the energy and related sectors, enabling our clients to make the best decisions within a constantly evolving global energy industry.

We are looking for a Power Market Analyst or Senior Analyst (depending on qualifications) to join our dynamic and expanding team in Sydney. The successful candidate will join our cross-technology team in downtown Sydney and be responsible for power market analysis, thought leadership and client engagement, and business development for the Australia market. He or she will use cutting-edge power dispatch models, engage industry executives on key market trends and forecasts, and deliver high-impact and original research to clients.

Joining a global team of over 100 power and renewables experts, you will quickly contribute to our power research in Asia Pacific. You will analyse the impact of latest policies and investments with our regional power models, develop technology and power price outlooks, coordinate with experts and stakeholders to optimise forecasts, and work on latest modelling advances such as battery revenue outlooks.

With guidance and reasonable inputs from the Research Director, you will also independently prepare high-quality, insightful reports, publications and presentations to influence clients’ business decisions. Through research trips, client interactions and industry events you will have opportunity to build and maintain relationships with a range of clients and other experts in the power & renewables industry. You will stay informed on key market trends and implement the latest ideas into power modelling and research reports. You will also play an important role in our commercial strategy including building new content, and managing teams to support global and local clients manage investments in the Australian market.

This role includes industry-leading skills training and learning opportunities and has excellent career development potential for thought leadership, power modelling and strategy roles in the power & renewables industry.

Main Responsibilities

 * Thought leadership and analysis of the Australia power & renewables market
 * Managing and updating regional power dispatch models and price forecasts
 * Engage clients and industry leaders to understand market trends and solve challenges

#LI-HH1


Qualifications


The role is ideal for an experienced professional who has a high aptitude for quantitative analysis and modelling, is passionate about understanding the big picture trends in the energy industry, and is looking to develop a career as a recognized power sector expert. The successful candidate will be expected to have the following qualities, qualifications and experience:

 * High interest and aptitude for market analysis and power modelling, preferably with related work experience. Relevant on-the-job training will be given to the selected candidate.
 * 2-5 years of relevant work experience in an analytical role in the power & renewables industry such as a utility, developer, consultancy or investor. A good understanding of power markets, technologies and company strategies is of high value.
 * Enthusiasm, curiosity, willingness to expand knowledge and skills, the ability to tackle challenging questions and to rethink conventional wisdom.
 * A bachelor’s degree in a relevant discipline such as engineering, science, economics, finance or other area. A graduate degree is preferred but not required.
 * Strong Excel skills. Relevant experience in data and database management is a major plus.
 * Programming and database management skills are a plus
 * Strong organisation, planning and time management skills
 * Effective writing and presentation skills
 * Strong attention to detail
 * Fluency in English is mandatory; fluency in another Asian language is a plus


Additional Information


“Wood Mackenzie is a place where we are committed to supporting our people to grow and thrive. We value different perspectives and aspire to create an inclusive environment which encourages diversity and fosters a sense of belonging.

Wood Mackenzie values everyone’s contribution and helps them reach their full potential while sustaining an organisational culture of health and well-being.

Our core values are:

 * Inclusive – we succeed together
 * Trusting – we choose to trust each other
 * Customer committed – we put customers at the heart of our decisions
 * Future Focused – we accelerate change
 * Curious – we turn knowledge into action

We understand the importance of bringing your whole self to work and to achieving balance between work, family and other life commitments. We are open to considering flexible working arrangements to enable the greatest spectrum of talent to contribute to Wood Mackenzie's success.

We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced Data Management Analyst with specialist expertise in Data Quality. This role will play a crucial part in ensuring the accuracy, consistency, and reliability of our data assets, focusing on critical data elements, data controls, data rules, data dictionaries, and metadata management. As a Data Management Analyst, you will play a crucial role in ensuring the effective management and governance of our clients data assets. Your main responsibilities will include implementing and maintaining data quality rules, metrics and dashboards, collaborating with cross-functional teams, and leveraging your technical proficiency in Data Quality tools such as IDQ to develop and enhance domain data dictionaries.
Responsibilities:

 * Collaborate with stakeholders to identify critical data elements and define business rules and data standards for their validation and verification.
 * Develop and implement data quality checks, controls, and validation routines to ensure the accuracy, completeness, and consistency of critical data elements.
 * Design and maintain data dictionaries to document data definitions, lineage, and usage across the organization.
 * Provide guidelines for structuring business metadata (e.g. business definitions, security/access levels, data quality rules) and technical metadata (e.g. technical/physical data elements, data lineage), where required.
 * Establish data quality metrics and KPIs to measure and monitor the effectiveness of data quality processes and identify areas for improvement.
 * Conduct data profiling and analysis to identify data quality issues, root causes, and remediation strategies.
 * Work closely with data stewards and subject matter experts to resolve data quality issues and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements.
 * Develop and maintain metadata repositories to capture and manage metadata attributes, relationships, and dependencies.
 * Provide training and support to end-users on data quality best practices, tools, and techniques.
 * Locate and define new process improvement opportunities in the sourcing, management of enterprise data.
 * Develop data lineage and metadata ingestion for prioritised data assets.

Requirements:

 * Experience working within Data Governance programs.
 * Very strong familiarity with metadata issues, processes and practices.
 * Experience in system mapping/ source to target data mapping.
 * Experience defining, implementing and managing business glossaries and data dictionaries.
 * Strong project co-ordination experience.
 * Strong interpersonal communication and persuasion skills.
 * Strong skills in data management technology including metadata management, data lineage and data quality tools.
 * Experience maintaining metadata management tools, including developing data lineage and managing technical/ business metadata.
 * Experience building and maintaining Data Quality reports.
 * Proficiency in data profiling tools, data quality tools, and metadata management tools.
 * Certification in data management (e.g., CDMP, DMBOK) or data quality (e.g., CIMP) is a plus.
 * Familiarity with data governance frameworks (e.g., DAMA-DMBOK ).

Our mission and where you fit in

We're a team of global innovators, who cherish diverse perspectives that fuel our mission; to simplify the world of work for SMBs worldwide.

As a cornerstone of Employment Hero's Revenue Growth & Insights team, the Commercial Insights Analyst serves as the analytical engine powering our data-driven commercial strategy. Reporting to the Head of Revenue Growth & Insights, this role centres on developing advanced data assets, analytics, and insights that guide key commercial decisions and strategies.

 * Develop and maintain sophisticated data models and dashboards, particularly focusing on commercial operations.

 * Engage with GTM and other commercial teams to integrate data insights into actionable commercial strategies.

What will you bring

 * Bachelor's degree in Data Analytics, Data Science, Business, or related field, or equivalent professional experience.
 * 5+ years of experience in an analytical role, preferably within a SaaS environment.
 * Advanced proficiency in SQL, and BI tools, especially Tableau.
 * Strong commercial acumen
 * Ability to translate business requirements & questions into technical solutions, and translate those solutions into actionable commercial insights
 * Proven track record of influencing decision-making processes through data-driven insights.
 * Exceptional ability to extract insights and support strategy development
 * Ability to work in a high-paced, dynamically changing environment where ruthless prioritisation is a necessity.

 * Ability to work cross functionally and foster strong partnerships
 * Previous experience working with Sales & Marketing SaaS metrics (e.g. MQL, SQL, SAL, SAO, MRR, ARR) highly regarded, as is experience working with CX metrics (e.g. NPS, CSAT)

What we're looking for

Apply -> Online Assessments -> Recruiter Interview -> Technical Interview -> Final Round Interviews -> Offer!

We encourage applications from candidates from all backgrounds, and we welcome requests for reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process to ensure that you can best demonstrate your abilities. If you have any questions, please contact sydneycampus@sig.com.




About SIG

SIG is a global quantitative trading firm founded by a group of friends who share a passion for game theory and probabilistic thinking. We have incorporated this approach into our culture, where you will find relentless problem solvers within each of our core disciplines: Trading, Technology, and Quantitative Research. From offices around the world, our employees collaborate to make optimal decisions and are driven by the desire to achieve winning results together.



What we do

We are experts in trading essentially all listed financial products and asset classes, with a focus on derivatives trading. Through market making and market taking, we handle millions of trading transactions around the world every day, providing liquidity and ensuring competitive prices for buyers and sellers. While our presence in the market is broad, our trading desks are highly specialized, allowing for a deep understanding of unique drivers of each asset class.

AIR6500 is the RAAF’s $3 billion program to develop a joint air battle management system that builds on the capabilities offered by Next Generation sensor and command and control systems. AIR6500 will create a fully networked ‘system of systems’ that synchronises air and missile defence operations in joint and coalition environments, maximising situational awareness and enhancing the speed of decision making across the battlespace.


Your responsibilities will include:

The Senior Configuration & Data Management (CDM) Analyst is part of a team that implements and supports a contemporary CDM solution, that takes advantage of digital environment capabilities and minimises transactional effort.

Some key responsibilities include;

 * Implement CDM plans that support both a Agile DevSecOps methodology and CDM activity outcomes as required by the contract
 * Apply the processes and procedures for the identification, control and distribution of project data

 * Advanced experience/ability using Microsoft Excel.
 * Familiarity with GIS mapping software.
 * Excellent communication skills.
 * Self-motivated with the ability to work independently and as part of a team

AVS works directly with a selection of the most strategic Retail vendors (supplier partners) to improve the value, selection and convenience across their Amazon business. Our team creates and innovates across brands, processes and people to grow business results and improve Vendor engagement and satisfaction.

We are seeking highly motivated Brand Analysts, who will act as Strategic Account Managers, owning the client-facing relationship with these supply partners and serve in an e-commerce capacity to drive their success, including growing revenue, improving operational efficiencies, executing initiatives and driving traffic and conversion. In this role, you will influence building and executing joint business plans with your Vendor, and collaborating with them to explore innovative merchandising, operational, and selection improvement opportunities.

The ideal candidate for this role should possess strong analytical, account management and/or vendor management skills. They should be able to deliver on commitments, manage workflows in a fast-paced work environment and actively participate in contributing to continuous improvement initiatives. Above all, they should demonstrate a high level of ownership and ability to navigate ambiguity. If you are interested in growing Amazon’s top brands, then we’re interested in you!

Key job responsibilities
Commencing in January or July 2024 (or earlier if available), as a Brand Analyst you will gain experience and a wide range of responsibilities, including;

 * Identify, action, and/or provide advice on how to improve business input metrics that drive growth and improve end customer experience in collaboration with other Amazon programs and teams.
 * Execute tactical support requests for Vendor, such as issue troubleshooting, data reporting, supply chain and catalogue management. Following up and escalating as appropriate to get these resolved in a timely manner.
 * Demonstrate excellent time-management skills and the ability to work independently while using centralized resources sand procedures.
 * Build strong relationship with the Vendor; be a trusted advisor and the central contact for their issues, questions, requests, escalations, and concerns.
 * Liaise with other internal departments as necessary to resolve Vendor issues and questions quickly and with high quality.
 * Teach Vendors how to be more successful on Amazon through training them on Amazon tools and policies and educating them on relevant growth opportunities in Amazon’s ecosystem of products.
 * Collaborating and exploring innovative ways to identify and execute new product selection, brand management, promotional strategies, operational efficiencies and reporting analysis for your vendors.
 * Working with varied stakeholders across AVS and wider Amazon teams such as Vendor and Category Managers, Instock, Finance, Operations, Marketing to drive best possible outcomes for your strategic vendors and customers.
 * Leading planning and performance sessions with your strategic vendors, and act as their main point of contact at Amazon.

To achieve success in this role, you will possess:

 * A natural appetite for learning and the ability to pick up new skills quickly

job_title: Analyst, Balance Sheet Risk, Modelling & Insights
job_description:
About the role

The Balance Sheet Risk, Modelling and Insights team (BSRMI) at Heritage and People’s Choice includes interest rate risk, liquidity risk, FX risk, wholesale credit risk and ICAAP plus responsibilities around risk modelling and insights.

In this role you will provide cross-functional support to ensure that our organisation operates consistently within our risk appetite. Reporting to the Head of Balance Sheet Risk, Risk Modelling and Insights, you will support senior members of the team with the management of the balance sheet risk management framework including related policies, risk tolerance monitoring, reporting and analytical support.

Overall, your key responsibilities will include contributing to the following core streams:

 * Supporting the team in reviewing regulatory requirements and best practice, assess coverage of these in policy and processes, then giving recommendations towards improvement
 * Supporting the maintenance of elements of the risk management methodologies, frameworks and models for key balance sheet risks (including Liquidity, Market Risk).
 * Monitoring line 1 compliance with balance sheet risk across the organisation and escalate any issues or incidents to Risk Leaders.
 * Supporting discussions and financial modelling with other departments’ (Treasury and Finance) leaders on balance sheet topics.
 * Analysing and contributing to reports on selected deep dive topics as directed.
 * Supporting the implementation of a contemporary stress testing framework including researching and developing stress scenarios, metrics and limits.
 * Participating in the evaluation of new products and business having the potential to affect HPC balance sheet and financial risk profile.
 * Supporting the work undertaken by senior members in the team around the Internal Capital Adequacy Assessment Process (ICAAP) including the Capital Management Policy, and capital assessment of material risks.
 * Performing analysis and reviews supporting model validation (not limited to balance sheet risk) as directed.
 * Contributing to the maintenance of the model validation framework.
 * Executing specific line 2 assurance tasks.Proactively identify risks and recommend actions to avoid, mitigate or accept risks.
 * Promoting a sound risk culture by routinely escalating risks including supporting analysis, plus recommendations on avoiding, mitigating or accepting risks.

About you

We’re looking for someone with at least 3 years’ experience in treasury or risk management with strong financial modelling capability. This will need to be in a medium to large but diverse organisation where you have had exposure to the use of financial modelling.

You will need to be a strong communicator with exceptional ability to translate complex information into an easy-to-understand format. Your experience and knowledge of contemporary strategic finance and treasury practices and trends will set you up for success as will a degree qualification in Commerce, Economics, Business, or a related discipline.

Additionally, you will relish the opportunity to positively influence the wider business through education and driving a strong risk and controls culture. Your work history will also demonstrate:

 * Experience in one or more of risk modelling, balance sheet analysis, treasury management including with bank regulation (APRA)
 * Excellent interpersonal, verbal, and written communication skills and ability to negotiate and influence senior stakeholders using non-technical language
 * Experience and/or knowledge of contemporary market and treasury risk management practices
 * Good understand of financial market and derivative products and their application for risk management
 * Experience in writing and developing business documents

Who are we?

It's an exciting time to join our organisation! On 1 March 2023, two of Australia's most successful member-owned banking organisations merged, to form Heritage and People's Choice - Australia's leading mutual banking organisation and a genuine, member-owned alternative to the major banks.

We are 100% member owned, with approximately 720,000 members and 1,900 employees. We have dual head offices in Adelaide and Toowoomba, and 95 branches across South Australia, Victoria, New South Wales, Queensland and the Northern Territory, trading under two brands, Heritage Bank and People's Choice.

When you come to work at Heritage and People's Choice, you'll be joining a team of inclusive, friendly, and motivated employees who value making a difference every day for our members, community, and the planet. We are committed to creating an outstanding working environment where you feel supported, can continue to develop and are proud advocates of our members and our business.

Benefits of working for us

We believe the little extras can make a big difference in supporting your success. That's why we offer great incentives and benefits including:

 * Work from anywhere philosophy with the flexibility to work from home or in the office
 * Career development opportunities, and ongoing training, coaching and support
 * A dedicated Employee Assistance Program for you and your family to access in times of need
 * Paid volunteering days and access to a diverse range of community and charitable initiatives

If this sounds like you, then this is the next step in your career. Click 'Apply' now and submit your application, including a cover letter and current resume by Thursday, 29 February 2024 .

We are committed to diversity and inclusion and support candidate requests for adjustments to accommodate disability, illness or injury, to enable everyone to equitably participate in our selection process.

Do you want to be part of Australia’s next FinTech Unicorn? At ROBOBAI, we’re empowering organizations to make intelligent, ethical decisions and be a force for good. We do this by delivering real-time actionable intelligence on the social and ethical risks and spend opportunities in supply chains. Our business intelligence platform leverages the power of AI and other technologies to integrate and digitize processes and systems across finance, procurement, and sustainability teams – to provide a 360-degree view of spend and deep insight into suppliers. Founded in 2017 Robobai is currently in high growth mode with active plans to penetrate further into the US and UK markets. This is an exciting opportunity to be part of that growth story and be part of the founding team. You should join us if you can think independently, be creative, and want to enjoy the opportunities for growth provided by a start-up company.

What We Offer

 * Flexible working Environment
 * Exposure to cutting-edge technologies and mentoring from industry leaders.
 * Ample of opportunities to learn and grow.
 * Generous Pay Package.
 * Company Stock options (ESOPS)

What will you be doing?

This position is responsible for ensuring that all deliveries of Robobai software products are in alignment with functional requirements and of a high calibre as determined by internal and external stakeholders. The role will be in charge of organizing the many forums' and stakeholders' activities required to make sure that the product's function, design, and development are in alignment. The position will manage those responsible for assessing and documenting requirements so that product development teams can successfully execute them.

 * You responsible for gathering business requirements and identifying Business content objects.
 * You will Create/maintain project plans for the team necessary to balance workloads across the delivery.
 * Based on Gap analysis, identifying the necessary customized reports and the BW objects required to meet the business requirement.
 * Recommend appropriate scope of requirements and priorities - Identifying and evaluating inefficiencies and recommending optimal business practices.
 * Work with architects to translate requirements into technical specifications involved in - the integration process, procedures, and functional requirements.
 * Contributing inputs to sprint planning, working with Development teams, to ensure delivery estimates accurately reflect functional scope.
 * Implement procurement analytics expertise to productize various optimization methodologies Viz. Vendor Rationalization, Price Variance, volume consolidation etc.
 * Responsible for defect management and ensuring that defects are assigned to the appropriate team member for timely resolution.
 * Validate and QA classification output of various Artificial intelligence (AI) models.
 * Overall management of product definition artifacts - functional designs, JIRA stories, test cases, test data definition and other related information
 * Productizing the token classification process to effectively categorize the large set of spend data.
 * Proficient in procurement processes, process optimization, and compliance improvement with data-driven analytics.
 * Working with various teams to create a successful solution, including the design and development team, sales and marketing, Q/A, and others, the manager of the product analyst teams and test resources is accountable for defining and validating the product quality.
 * Providing functional support for end-to-end SDLC lifecycle.
 * Responsible for conducting Knowledge Sharing Sessions for Business Analysts, Developers and Users on complex business processes.

What We’re Looking For

 * >10 years in a consulting role, product development/delivery environment with deep experience in the definition of business requirements and software quality control
 * Spend Analytics experience preferably from GP or Zycus or similar.
 * Diverse experience of using various P2P platforms Viz. I- Analyze, Ariba, Watson, IBM Emptoris etc.
 * Strong team leadership/line management experience
 * Ability to successfully work with external and internal stakeholders to establish and validate product functional needs.
 * Ability to successfully work across the organization – Product, UX Design and Development team resources to ensure application design and requirements alignment.
 * Ability to prioritize and maintain focus and delivery in a high-paced development environment.
 * Ability to identify and remediate potential gaps/issues early to ensure they are addressed quickly.
 * Excellent written and verbal communication skills ensuring clarity in understanding of requirements across stakeholders.
 * Ability to communicate and summarise requirements effectively to other team members to get the right outcomes.
 * Technology-based degree or equivalent qualifications.
 * Preferred experience in procurement-based or analytics platform environments
 * CSPO – Certified
 * BSI-certified ISO practitioner.

If this sounds like you please submit a CV and cover letter addressing the above criteria.

A future with ASIC means that your work will contribute to ASIC's vision for a fair, strong and efficient financial system for all Australians. We value what you will bring. We value those with sharp, analytical minds and are open to challenging the way things are done.

The team
Market Supervision seeks to ensure trust and confidence in Australia's financial markets by regulating market intermediaries (including market participants, investment banks, securities dealers and issuers of over the counter (OTC) products). We also carry out surveillances of Australia's listed and OTC markets and test our stakeholder's compliance with the law.
Market Supervision's Market Surveillance team is primarily responsible for real time market surveillance and for ensuring that those who participate in the market comply with all relevant obligations under the Corporations Act 2001, Australian Financial Services Licence (AFSL) regime and the ASIC Market Integrity Rules. The team also works closely with other ASIC teams to address market misconduct matters and provides advice to those teams in relation to markets and trading related matters.
The role
As a Market Analyst in the Market Supervision Team, you will report to the Senior Manager, Market Supervision and:


 * undertake surveillance and assessment of listed market misconduct, including administration of Continuous Disclosure, Insider Trading and Market Manipulation provisions.
 * develop and maintain relationships with key internal and external stakeholders including self-regulatory organisations, particularly Australian Market Operators such as ASX and Cboe.
 * research and analyse emerging and current regulatory issues in relation to financial markets and assist in the design and implementation of projects to address them.
 * conduct real-time market surveillance to identify serious market misconduct and breaches of ASIC Market Integrity Rules.
 * participate in multi-skilled cross-stakeholder team projects.

About you


 * A relevant degree in finance, commerce, accounting or law and/or equivalent substantial relevant work experience.
 * Knowledge of (or ability to acquire knowledge of) the Market Integrity Rules, Corporations Act and AFSL conditions insofar as they relate to financial services intermediaries, market manipulation, insider trading and continuous disclosure obligations.
 * Ability to understand and analyse trading patterns.
 * Knowledge of (or ability to acquire knowledge of) legislation, policies and procedures relevant to the functions of ASIC.
 * Experience in effectively presenting complex information to different target audiences through strong business writing and verbal communication skills.

About ASIC
ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world.
ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system.
Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.
Through Moneysmart, we aim to improve the skills and knowledge of Australians and provide information and tools to help them in their decision making.
A future with ASIC means that your work will contribute to achieving ASIC's vision for a fair, strong, and efficient financial system for all Australians.
ASIC is committed to a providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.

THE OPPORTUNITY





 * Take your career to the next level within an incredible team!
 * Inform business decision-making through data driven insight
 * Lead market analysis projects working alongside science teams at CSIRO




As the Market Analyst you will play an important role in providing enterprise level market intelligence support to various groups across CSIRO.




You will play a vital role, providing high quality market, industry, customer and competitive analysis and insights; and drawing conclusions that will inform business decision-making in relation to the market landscape, as well as providing information to help align key research areas with industry.




This is a genuinely meaningful role which will support researchers’ decision-making processes about future commercial pathways for their research and technology.




While demonstrating proficiency working autonomously, you will sit alongside great people and market analysts within the Business Engagement Solutions Team (BEST) which reports into the Strategic Delivery Business Unit, CSIRO Growth.


YOUR DUTIES WILL INCLUDE:

 * Leading market analysis projects by working alongside science teams to source, evaluate, synthesise and analyse a broad range of qualitative and quantitative data.

 * Forming insights, providing written business reports and analysis that can be included as input to decision-making about research & technology pathways.

 * Providing support to the Commercialisation team through market scoping.

 * Managing stakeholder engagement, presenting results to internal teams and workshops, facilitating market-related discussions.

 * Contributing to a team environment that values equity and diversity and enables the achievement of personal objectives, team and organisational KPIs, including adhering to the spirit and practice of CSIRO’s values, HSE policies and diversity initiatives.

 * Other duties and tasks that may arise as priorities for the team and for Growth.

The work is based around secondary desktop research and does not require the applicant to source primary data or undertake field trips to perform the role.




Location: CSIRO Sites in all AU Major Cities will be considered. A hybrid working environment is available.

Reference: 95990


TO BE CONSIDERED YOU WILL NEED:

 * Tertiary or PhD qualification\s in science, business & commerce and\or relevant experience in technology commercialisation.

 * Demonstrated proficiency in report writing, presentation and communication.

 * Demonstrated skills and understanding of data retrieval techniques and market analysis.

 * Interest in markets, business, science trends and innovation.

 * An MBA and previous experience with market analysis databases is desirable.

 * We are preferably looking for someone with a scientific background and broad interest across many science disciplines, combined with a high level of business & commercial acumen.
   



For full details about this role please view the Position Description


ELIGIBILITY

Applications for this position are open to Australian/New Zealand Citizens and Australian Permanent Residents. Appointment to this role is subject to provision of a national police check.


FLEXIBLE WORKING ARRANGEMENTS

We work flexibly at CSIRO, offering a range of options for how, when and where you work.


DIVERSITY AND INCLUSION

We are working hard to recruit people representing the diversity across our society, and ensure that all our people feel supported to do their best work and feel empowered to let their ideas flourish.


ABOUT CSIRO

At CSIRO Australia's national science agency, we solve the greatest challenges through innovative science and technology. We put the safety and wellbeing of our people above all else and earn trust everywhere because we only deal in facts. We collaborate widely and generously and deliver solutions with real impact.




CSIRO is committed to values-based leadership to inspire performance and unlock the potential of our people.



Join us and start creating tomorrow today!

job_description:
Opportunity snapshot:

An exciting, permanent opportunity has become available for a Senior Business Intelligence Data Operations Analyst.

The Health Insurance Business Intelligence (HI BI) Data Operations team is undergoing changes and is looking to expand its influence into multiple teams. With this change comes the expansion of the Data Operations role to include governance and quality, ensuring that the HI BI team have controls in place to confidently report critical figures to the Health Insurance Business Unit.

Reporting to the Business Intelligence Operations, Governance & Quality Manager, the Senior Data Operations Analyst ensures the stability and timely delivery of a broad suite of existing reporting assets and dashboards as well as the ingestion of new reports from the wider Business Intelligence & Reporting team. This role will require the individual to think strategically and adopt a continuous improvement mindset to further the scope of the operations team to include Data Governance and Data Quality.

How will I help?

 * Supporting the maintenance and optimisation of a complex suite of reporting and business intelligence assets by utilising a broad range of technical tools
 * Mentorship and coaching of Junior Team members to ensure knowledge sharing through best practices, and encouragement of personal growth.
 * Develop strategies to influence our governance and quality standards into other teams
 * Maintaining key data reports, extracts and contributing to process improvements to ensure that the HI business can respond quickly to changing market demands.
 * Supporting the continuous improvement of processes and structures to ensure best practice for data operations.


What do I need?

 * Expertise in SAS, SSIS, Power BI, Synapse, VBA and Databricks suite necessary
 * Highly experienced in data analytics, data quality, data governance, data warehousing and reporting
 * Strong business acumen with strong written and verbal communication skills & ability to engage stakeholders at all levels
 * 5+ years technical knowledge and skills across the Microsoft Data Platforms & Data Analytics
 * 5+ years of hands-on experience using SQL to extract and manipulate data for reporting and insights
 * 2+ years of experience using Microsoft Power BI (including DAX coding)
 * Demonstrated ability to present to large groups, conveying technical concepts.
 * Tertiary qualifications in Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science or a related quantitative field
 * Expertise in analysing data sets, quantitative analysis, data mining, predictive modelling and creating data visualisations

 * Support for Access - Help leaders in ensuring easy access to data for people that they work with
 * Empowerment - Enabling business people to do their role as owners, stewards, and leaders.
 * Delivery & Customer Value First - Treat data as an asset to create value for customers and remove barriers to achieving compliance, risk, or other barriers to value



What’s in it for you?

As well as a competitive salary, a range of Bupa benefits and flexible working/ work from home, you’ll be challenged and encouraged to innovate. You will collaborate strongly with colleagues who are committed to delivering exceptional experiences. We trust, respect and consider everyone, knowing your difference will make the difference.

Other benefits include subsidies on our health insurance, travel, car, home, contents and pet insurance products as well as Bupa services such as Dental and Optical. You can also access a ‘People First’ wellness program which provides a range of services such as health coaches, annual skin checks and flu vaccinations, assistance with nutrition, mental and general well-being guides and product discounts.

You’ll feel happier & healthier working at Bupa!

We are one of Australia's leading retail property groups, who are reimagining the way Australians live, work and play. We own and manage some of the most recognisable and loved retail destinations across Australia and are evolving to transform our portfolio into destinations that offer a broad selection of retail, residential, and office spaces.

Role purpose
The key purpose of the Technical Business Analyst role is to analyse and translate business requirements to detailed technical specifications that guide the solution development process.

Key Responsibilities
Requirements Elicitation:
 * Collaborate with business stakeholders to understand their needs, goals, and objectives
 * Elicit and document detailed business requirements, ensuring a clear understanding of the desired outcomes


Analysis and Documentation:
 * Analyse and document business processes, systems, and workflows
 * Create process models, data models, and other relevant documentation to illustrate future states


Technical Solution Design:
 * Work with the project team to translate business requirements into technical specifications
 * Collaborate with architects and developers to design technical solutions that align with business objectives


Data Analysis:
 * Conduct data analysis to understand data structures, sources, and dependencies
 * Define data requirements and support data modeling efforts


Prototyping and Mockups:
 * Develop prototypes or mockups to demonstrate proposed system features or changes, as required
 * Gather feedback from stakeholders to refine and improve solution designs


User Acceptance Testing (UAT) Support:

 * Assist in UAT execution, ensuring that the final solution meets business requirements


Risk Analysis:
 * Identify and assess potential risks associated with technical solutions
 * Work with the project team to develop risk mitigation strategies


Documentation Management:

 * Ensure that documentation is accessible to relevant stakeholders


Communication and Collaboration:
 * Facilitate communication between business and technical teams
 * Collaborate with developers, architects, and other project stakeholders to ensure a shared understanding of requirements


Change Management:
 * Support the change management process by identifying the impact of proposed changes on existing processes and systems
 * Assist in developing and implementing plans to manage the transition to new systems or processes


Continuous Improvement:
 * Identify opportunities for process improvement and optimization
 * Provide feedback on lessons learned and contribute to the improvement of project methodologies


Training and Support:
 * Collaborate with training teams to develop materials and resources for end-users
 * Provide support during the implementation phase and address user queries or concerns


Alignment with Business Strategy:
 * Ensure that proposed technical solutions align with the overall business and IT strategy
 * Provide recommendations for technology or process improvements that support strategic goals


Key Role Relationships
 * Business Analyst
 * Product Owner
 * Business Lead
 * Process Lead


Capability and Experience

Business Analysis Skills:
 * Requirements Gathering: Proficient in techniques for eliciting and documenting business requirements, such as interviews, surveys, workshops, and use cases
 * Business Process Modelling: Ability to model and analyse business processes using tools like BPMN (Business Process Model and Notation)


Technical Proficiency:
 * Understanding of Systems Architecture: Familiarity with systems architecture and the ability to understand how different components of a system interact
 * Data Analysis: Ability to analyse data requirements and design data models
 * Technical Documentation: Proficient in creating detailed technical documentation, including specifications, data dictionaries, and system diagrams


Communication Skills:
 * Stakeholder Communication: Strong communication skills to facilitate effective communication between business stakeholders and the technical team
 * Documentation Skills: Clear and concise writing skills for creating comprehensive and understandable documentation
 * Presentation Skills: Ability to present technical information to both technical and non-technical audiences


Analytical Skills:
 * Problem-Solving: Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to analyse complex business problems and propose effective solutions
 * Critical Thinking: The ability to think critically and evaluate the impact of proposed solutions on both business processes and technical systems


Project Management Skills:
 * Project Coordination: Ability to coordinate with project managers, developers, and other stakeholders to ensure the successful delivery of projects
 * Timeline Management: Experience in managing timelines and ensuring that project milestones are met


Collaboration and Teamwork:
 * Cross-Functional Collaboration: Ability to work collaboratively with cross-functional teams, including developers, QA teams, and business stakeholders
 * Team Facilitation: Experience in facilitating discussions and workshops to gather requirements and make decisions


Technical Knowledge:
 * Programming Knowledge: Basic understanding of programming languages and technologies would be beneficial
 * Database Understanding: Familiarity with database concepts and SQL queries
 * Integration Knowledge: Understanding of system integrations and API interactions


Quality Assurance:
 * Testing Knowledge: Understanding of testing processes and the ability to collaborate with QA teams to ensure that solutions meet specified requirements


Adaptability:
 * Adaptability to Change: Ability to adapt to changing project requirements, priorities, technologies, and business landscape


Industry and Domain Knowledge:
 * Industry Understanding: Familiarity with retail property management, including understanding market trends, competition, and regulatory considerations
 * Regulatory Knowledge: Awareness of regulatory requirements that may impact business processes and technical solutions


Continuous Learning:
 * Stay Informed: Proactively stay informed about emerging technologies, industry trends, and best practices in business analysis


Education and Certifications:
 * Relevant Degree: A degree in business, information technology, or a related field
 * Certifications: Relevant certifications in business analysis or related areas (e.g. CBAP - Certified Business Analysis Professional)


Interpersonal Skills:
 * Negotiation and Conflict Resolution: Ability to negotiate priorities and resolve conflicts that may arise during the analysis process

Opportunity snapshot:

An exciting, fixed term opportunity has become available for a Senior Data Analyst.

As part of critical in-flight Remediation programs, this role will work with the Remediation team and Operational teams to conduct the discovery and delivery work associated with the remediation & rectification programs. Understanding the scale, scope of any impacted customer cohort, along with the understanding of system or conduct failures is critical to delivery of rectification and remediation efforts.

This role will support data analysis activities in customer remediation within the Health Insurance business, helping ensure that Bupa puts things right for impacted customers efficiently and fairly.
Working in an agile environment across multiple projects with multiple stakeholders and business units, this role will support project teams in the extraction, curation and analysis of data in relation to remediation activities, to ensure the scope of impacted customers is accurate and the remediation methodology is being applied correctly.

The Senior Data Analyst will also perform scenario testing, quality assurance activities and ensure that all data rules, logic and code used are documented into a consistent, standardised format. This role will perform an integral role in the continuous improvement and uplift of Bupa’s remediation capability.

How will I help?

 * Working within a project team, partner closely with business and technical SMEs to develop a deep understanding of the remediation activity, including products, systems, with a strong focus on source data environments
 * Translate the business rules for a remediation activity into clear, accurate data rules and write SQL code based on these data rules to extract relevant data from source systems
 * Design and build data management processes and tools to support remediation objectives, including management of scope, reporting & process performance.
 * Support remediation project managers providing relevant business & data analysis.


What do I need?

 * Experience in remediation projects or programs, or complex customer-facing transformation projects.
 * Previous experience in customer remediation delivery working in a data analyst capacity
 * Experience translation of business rules into clear, accurate data rules. Delivery of business rules in SQL data rules to extract relevant information from tactical and strategic data stores.
 * Proficient knowledge of data extraction and analysis from large databases using tools such as SQL, SAS, power Bi etc.
 * Strong competency with using MS Excel to perform data analysis/scenario testing
 * Tertiary qualifications in Information Systems/Information Technology or similar
 * Analytical and problem-solving skills, with a strong attention to detail

The University of Western Australia (UWA) is ranked among the top 100 universities in the world and a member of the prestigious Australian Group of Eight research intensive universities. With a strong research track record, vibrant campus and working environments, supported by the freedom to innovate and inspire, there is no better time to join Western Australia’s top university.

About the team

The Brand, Marketing and Recruitment (BMR) division exists for the purpose of showcasing the best of UWA, ultimately enhancing reputation and driving student recruitment. The division consolidates all marketing, communications and future student related activity into one team, enabling efficiency and effectiveness gains for the University.

Functions delivered by the BMR division include organisational wide brand strategy and management, strategic marketing planning, communications activities (advertising, marketing, content, media, public relations); digital communication, reputation management, recruitment planning, business development, schools engagement, contact centre operations and admissions services. The range of functions delivered are all targeted at managing the University’s reputation and achieving its revenue goals.

The Marketing Insight and Analytics team within BMR analyses data and creates actionable insights to inform data-driven strategies, plans, tactical student acquisition opportunities and decision-making. Functions delivered by the Marketing Insight and Analytics team include:

 * Data strategy, including databases to store, profile and target leads.
 * Customer Relationship Management (CRM) analysis and segment opportunity
 * identification.
 * Consumer insights to understand segments, their drivers and behaviour.
 * Marketing insight to review marketing/recruitment activity effectiveness (campaign,
 * channel).
 * Market research to track market and supply chain perceptions and intentions.
 * Environment and competitor monitoring and benchmarking.
 * Commercial analysis to support proposition development and business cases.

About the opportunity

As the appointee you will, under broad direction, provide senior analytical expertise in data management, particularly with data extract, transfer, load (ETL) and data governance to support BMR insight and analytics activities including diagnostic and predictive projects. This includes reporting, data governance, analysis and list generation to support conversion and marketing activities, warehousing, reporting/analysis of operational data, validating existing reporting structures and integrating new customer data sources.

About you

You have a passion for data science and business analytics in marketing. Using R language to conduct exploratory data analysis and model building on large datasets excite you. You must be competent and independent in constructing enterprise level MS SQL queries, extract & transform data by applying business logic, and create data pipeline/s to drive MS Power BI dashboards. You understand that your true value lies in using actionable insights to drive positive business impacts, and data, stats and tech are just a means to an end. The ideal you have a strong background in leveraging enterprise marketing automation and CRM platforms for higher education student recruitment at scale.

To be considered for this opportunity, you will demonstrate:

 * Relevant tertiary qualification in a mathematics/computing/data science field or demonstrated equivalent competency
 * Substantial relevant experience at an appropriate level
 * Proficiency in a high level programming language such as R or Python
 * Demonstrated capability to write SQL queries to extract data from relational databases
 * Proficiency in software libraries for data import, web requests, data cleaning and transformation, statistical modelling and data visualisation
 * Demonstrated experience merging, validating and curating datasets to support analytics and operations and in data governance, including handling of personally-identifiable information in a secure manner
 * Demonstrated expertise in segmentation techniques and in identification of business opportunities
 * Demonstrated ability to answer queries, write reports and present technical findings to a variety of non-technical stakeholders
 * Sound analytical skills with the ability to collect, organise, analyse, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy
 * Knowledge of university admissions (or similar) policies, procedures and data structures preferred but not required

Note: Occasional weekend work and some after hours work may be required.

Join the largest insurance group in Australia and New Zealand.

 * Community volunteer days and team volunteer activities
 * Join great employee network communities
 * Grow your financial future with 13% superannuation as standard

We’re ready for you. Apply today.


Learn more about who IAG is here

At CommBank we believe in working somewhere that works for you. We have many flexible working options available so talk to us about which arrangements could work best for you



You are a curious and enthusiastic Analyst with a true passion for data and analytics.

We are a close-knit team who use data to develop and enhance the Group’s fraud and scam reports and dashboards.

Together we will develop insights on fraud and scam trends to quantify their impacts on customer loss and the bank’s financial and operational performance.



See yourself in our team:

We are a diverse team who draw on one another’s experience to deliver to best work outcomes. We are committed to safe-guarding our customers from financial fraud and scams. We maintain the Group’s fraud detection algorithms through intelligent automation whilst studying emerging fraud trends and using these insights to improve fraud detection. Developing models of fraud behaviour.



Do work that matters:

The Group Fraud Management Services (GFMS) vision is to inspire confidence and create peace of mind. We strive to provide safe banking through prevention, detection and response. Group Fraud Management Services consists of Bankwest Financial Crime Services, Card Fraud, Digital Fraud, Branch Fraud, Originations & Scams, Fraud Capability Intel & Advisory, Analytics and Business Performance & Strategy. The Digital Fraud team is responsible for the detection and assessment of digital and mobile fraud and scam incidents.



On a day-to-day basis, you will:

 * Develop reports using the various tools such as SAS visual analytics, Tableau, Microsoft Office.

 * Develop interactive dashboards, reporting and visualisations, to provide insights and make recommendations.

 * Make continual improvements to detection system rules to ensure maximum detection occurs whilst false positive and point of detection remains low.

 * Ensure the effective operation of the digital fraud response centre teams to deliver to service level agreements and provide quality customer outcomes.

 * Maintain an up-to-date focus on digital Fraud & Scams related trends, emerging issues and control improvements.



We are interested in hearing from people who have:

Please note that we’re interested in hearing from people who might not meet all the following criteria. We’re open to working with the right candidate to fill any skill gaps during your journey at CommBank.

 * An analytical mindset with the ability to solve problems in a creative way.

 * Knowledge of visual reporting insights using Tableau.

 * Sound programming knowledge in SQL or SAS .

 * Ability to understand fraudster behaviour and psychology to improve fraud detection.

 * A degree in a quantitative discipline such as mathematics, statistics, computing, science, engineering or actuarial studies.



If this sounds like you then apply today!



If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest, x15ventures), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.

Where you’ll be working

The Cancer Institute NSW is the NSW Government’s cancer control agency, established to lessen the impact of cancer across the state.




Working at the Cancer Institute NSW means joining a team of committed and dedicated staff who are proud to be a part of the Institute’s purpose of overseeing and accelerating the effectiveness of cancer control in NSW.




The Cancer Institute is a collaborative working environment that encourages diversity and inclusion in how we work and the way we work together. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples are strongly encouraged to apply. Greater consideration will be given to suitable applicants, in order to improve access to employment and career opportunities (GSE Rule 26).




What you’ll be doing

The Cancer Institute NSW is seeking an experienced Data Analyst to join the Reporting and Analytics team within the Business Intelligence and Information Systems group to provide information and critical analyses that will aid in the provision and improvement of cancer screening services in NSW and support the achievement of Cancer Plan objectives.




The role of Data Analyst functions within our Reporting and Analytics team and is required to work collaboratively with stakeholders in the Screening & Prevention Division. You will ensure that requests for data information needs are delivered in a timely manner, as well as performing data analysis and development of reports and dashboards that aid in the provision and improvement of cancer screening services in NSW and support the achievement of our Cancer Plan objectives.




Essential to the role will be your ability to engage with and influence stakeholders to contribute to high quality cancer control programs for the people of NSW. You will be a team player that thrives in a collaborative, dynamic and evolving landscape to support the delivery of strategic information through to actionable insights.




For your application to be considered

To submit your application, please provide:

 * Your resume (maximum five pages)
 * A covering letter addressing the Essential Requirements, as outlined in the Role Description
 * A response to the Pre-screening questions, as outlined below.




Essential requirements

 * Tertiary qualifications in IT or a related discipline, actuarial studies or engineering, or demonstrated equivalent professional experience.
 * Proven experience in undertaking statistical data analysis and development of dashboards/reports on large datasets for the purpose of performance monitoring and improvement using data analysis tools, Business Intelligence tools (Power BI), advanced scripting in SQL and R programming.
 * Demonstrated experience in the planning and provision of training to support users in the use of reporting applications.
 * Demonstrated experience in analytical thinking and problem-solving skills, strong organisational skills and the ability to effectively manage and meet multiple competing priorities and deadlines.
 * Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively as part of a team and independently with minimal supervision.




If successful for interview candidates must bring original copies of essential qualifications to be sighted by the panel, and one copy to provide to panel.

Interested?

job_title: Product Data Scientist - Tiktok Data Analysis - Australia
job_description:
Responsibilities
About TikTok
TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo.

Why Join Us
Creation is the core of TikTok's purpose. Our platform is built to help imaginations thrive. This is doubly true of the teams that make TikTok possible.
Together, we inspire creativity and bring joy - a mission we all believe in and aim towards achieving every day.
To us, every challenge, no matter how difficult, is an opportunity; to learn, to innovate, and to grow as one team. Status quo? Never. Courage? Always.
At TikTok, we create together and grow together. That's how we drive impact - for ourselves, our company, and the communities we serve.

About the Team
The Product Data Analytics Team analyses a combination of product usage and product performance data to derive meaningful insights that would serve as a guide to better product and decision making for our business leaders. The team will work through different business scenarios including improving Live app Experiences, Host Operation, User experiences. In addition, it is important to manage the data life cycle to ensure problems are quantitatively measured to propose logical solutions.

Responsibilities:

 * Responsible for the data analytics work in international LIVE business, including but not limited to live gifts, host interaction, strategies, enhancing the live streaming revenue.
 * Identify and analyse key factors driving the growth of international LIVE, and propose enhancement plans with logical data support
 * Responsible for the design and analysis of A/B experiments, product iteration impact evaluation, marketing campaign analysis, key metrics trend analysis, etc
 * Work with cross functional partners like Product Managers, Operations, R&D for product optimisation plans and boost business growth
 * Perform market activity analysis and any other analytics that would help guide product and business in decision making.

Qualifications
1. Bachelor degree or above in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics or other related majors;
2. At least 3 years of experiences and above; Experience in supporting analytical work of internet or large scale C2C products is preferred;
3. Proficient in SQL, skilled use of visualisation tools
4. Experience in data extraction, analysis and visualisation in a complex data environment, and have experiences in data landing to the business
5. Excellent communication skills with ability to communicate conclusions effectively to both technical and non-technical audiences, and good analysis report writing ability;
6. Strong learning ability and curiosity driven mindset, independent and possess collaborative problem solving skills

TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.

In the spirit of reconciliation, TikTok acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their Elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.

There’s No Us Without U. Care with Us, for Today and Tomorrow

There's no life without water, and at Urban Utilities, we live and breathe that knowledge every single day. It's why our people are so passionate about what they do and how they do it. And it's why we need people like YOU. Come shape our future with us and make a real and lasting impact across our teams.

Your opportunity:

The Workforce Reporting & Data Analyst role is an integral new position, that will be responsible for building and developing a suite of workforce analytics and BI reporting. This will provide critical planning and management control tools used by our organisation’s leaders to assess and drive the effectiveness and efficiency of their workforce plans in a close as possible, real-time.

Using information and data collected from Payroll, HRIS, Scheduling and Finance systems you will bring logic and understanding to the data through detailed and complex investigation and reconciliations. You will partner closely with leaders across the organisation to ensure consistency and alignment of reporting & analysis and be able to present findings in a clear and meaningful display to make informed business decisions.

About you:

 * Experience in workforce planning, rostering and payroll reporting including complex data analysis and modelling techniques

 * Proficient user in R programming and Power BI tools or similar

 * Strong data analytical report building skills

 * Ability to collaborate with a variety if stakeholders across the organisational structure

 * Excellent facilitation and communication skills with the ability to present findings from data in a meaningful way

At UU, we celebrate diversity. We genuinely believe that bringing together diversity of thoughts, perspectives and expressions is key and crucial to our success as a business. You might find you meet some, but not all, of the job requirements for this role. We’d still encourage you to apply as we we’re looking for the right human being for this role - it’s about so much more than ticking all the boxes!




Why Urban Utilities?

At Urban Utilities, the work we do is about so much more than the bottom line. We're a leading provider of world-class drinking water and wastewater services to the vibrant communities of

Brisbane, Ipswich, Lockyer Valley, Somerset, and Scenic Rim. As we continue to grow, we're committed to planning ahead and shaping a sustainable future around water for generations to come.

At the core of our work lies genuine care: for our team, our customers, communities, and the environment. From the flush of a toilet to major infrastructure projects and residential developments, we're dedicated to being there every step of the way.

Our HQ is in Fortitude Valley, Brisbane, but you'll find us all over SEQ - working in cool places like the SAS Laboratory in Darra, field-based depots in Eagle Farm, Acacia Ridge, Bundamba, and wastewater treatment plants dotted across the region.

We know the chance to thrive, and progress comes hand in hand with the support to balance work with life. So, you’ll access an increasingly diverse range of benefits and initiatives that’ll help you bring the best you. Speaking of which, here’s just a sample of the benefits we offer our team:

 * Generous Salary Packaging options, including novated leases

 * Corporate discounts across Health insurance, technology and more

 * 18 weeks of paid parental leave, 15 days personal leave including two proactive wellbeing days, and an additional day of leave each year to connect with friends and family

 * Flexibility at UU depends on the type of work you do but could include options such as, 9-day fortnights and flexible days. Talk to us about what flexibility means to you!

 * Urban Utilities is an endorsed employer for all women. See our range of benefits and policies directly at WORK180 Visit our website to learn more about us at www.urbanutilities.com.au

Why Central Australian Aboriginal Congress?
Congress is the largest Aboriginal community-controlled health organisation in the Northern Territory and are one of the most experienced Aboriginal primary health care services in the country.




Congress provides a comprehensive, holistic and culturally-responsive primary health care service to Aboriginal people living in and nearby Alice Springs, including eight remote communities, it is a strong political advocate of closing the gap on Aboriginal health disadvantage and a national leader in improving health outcomes for all Aboriginal people.




Working with Central Australian Aboriginal Congress not only offers rewarding career options, but a wide range of employee benefits including;

 * Competitive salaries
 * Six (6) weeks' annual leave
 * Generous salary packaging
 * A strong commitment to Professional Development
 * Access to the Congress health services for you and your family at no cost
 * Relocation assistance (where applicable)
 * District allowance and Remote Benefits

About the role

The Health Informatics and Data Analytics Coordinator (HIDA) analyses, builds, and presents healthcare information to optimise service delivery and support Congress’ objectives by enabling data-driven decisions. They gather pertinent healthcare data, develop effective information systems and procedures, and supply decision makers and service providers with access to relevant and meaningful information. This position is a senior clinical data position at Congress and works in conjunction with the Health Information Manager.




For more information on the position please contact: Chief Medical Officer - Public Health, Dr. John Boffa on 0418 812 141 / 8951 4401 or john.boffa@caac.org.au
